{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780735931975,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"id":"prt_e9c21f645001rD5MsSSW37QOGn","messageID":"msg_e9c21eabc001M8dM0IAEcrr8aI","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","snapshot":"f99f735171c64f07bf9ef2ccd9597b2a4e2ae6d8","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735936622,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_esoIAS3mbD47Kv3bLz976465","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/SKILL.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: deep-research\n3: description: \"Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation, externalized state, convergence detection, fresh context per pass.\"\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, memory_context, memory_search]\n5: argument-hint: \"[topic] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N]\"\n6: version: 1.13.1.0\n7: ---\n8: \n9: <!-- Keywords: autoresearch, deep-research, iterative-research, autonomous-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, research-agent, JSONL-state, strategy-file -->\n10: \n11: # Autonomous Deep Research Loop\n12: \n13: Note: `Task` is allowed for the command executor that manages the loop. The `@deep-research` agent itself is LEAF-only and does not dispatch sub-agents.\n14: \n15: Iterative research protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, and convergence detection for deep technical investigation.\n16: \n17: Runtime path resolution:\n18: - OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n19: - Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n20: - Codex runtime: `.codex/agents/*.toml`\n21: \n22: Operator contract precedence for this skill surface:\n23: - Command entrypoint syntax in `.opencode/commands/deep/start-research-loop.md`\n24: - Convergence math in `references/convergence/convergence.md` and the deep-research YAML workflow\n25: - Runtime agent inventories from the checked-in runtime directories above\n26: \n27: ### Convergence Threshold Semantics\n28: \n29: **Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n30: \n31: **Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n32: \n33: **NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n34: - `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n35: - `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n36: \n37: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. See this skill's changelog and decision records for the cross-sibling threshold research and parity invariants that confirm thresholds do not carry across siblings.\n38: \n39: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\n40: \n41: ### Activation Triggers\n42: \n43: Use this skill when:\n44: - Deep investigation requiring multiple rounds of discovery\n45: - Topic spans 3+ technical domains or sources\n46: - Initial findings need progressive refinement\n47: - Overnight or unattended research sessions\n48: - Research where prior findings inform subsequent queries\n49: \n50: Keyword triggers:\n51: \n52: - `autoresearch`\n53: - `deep research`\n54: - `autonomous research`\n55: - `research loop`\n56: - `iterative research`\n57: - `multi-round research`\n58: - `deep investigation`\n59: - `comprehensive research`\n60: \n61: ### Use Cases\n62: \n63: Use deep-research for multi-round technical investigation, source triangulation, repeated exploration with fresh context, and research sessions where prior findings should shape the next focus.\n64: \n65: ### When NOT to Use\n66: \n67: - Simple, single-question research (use direct codebase search or `/speckit:plan`)\n68: - Known-solution documentation (use `/speckit:plan`)\n69: - Implementation tasks (use `/speckit:implement`)\n70: - Quick codebase searches (use `@context` or direct Grep/Glob)\n71: - Fewer than 3 sources needed (single-pass research suffices)\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## 2. SMART ROUTING\n76: \n77: > Pattern: aligned with the [sk-doc smart-router resilience template](../sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md).\n78: \n79: ### Resource Domains\n80: \n81: The router discovers markdown resources recursively from `references/` and `assets/`, then applies intent scoring from `RESOURCE_MAP`. Keep routing domain-focused rather than hardcoding exhaustive inventories.\n82: \n83: - `references/guides/quick_reference.md` for the first-touch operator cheat sheet.\n84: - `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` for lifecycle, dispatch, reducer sequencing, and command-owned state flow.\n85: - `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` for bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back.\n86: - `references/convergence*.md` for stop contracts, signals, recovery, graph gates, and reference-only convergence ideas.\n87: - `references/state*.md` for packet layout, JSONL records, markdown outputs, reducer ownership, and reconstruction.\n88: - `references/guides/capability_matrix.md` for runtime parity.\n89: - `assets/*.md` for markdown templates and prompt assets that are safe to route through guarded markdown loading.\n90: \n91: ### Resource Loading Levels\n92: \n93: | Level | When to Load | Resources |\n94: |-------|--------------|-----------|\n95: | ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | Quick reference baseline |\n96: | CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Loop, convergence, state, spec anchoring, runtime parity references |\n97: | ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request | Full reference set and markdown assets |\n98: \n99: ### Phase Signals\n100: \n101: | Phase | Signal | Primary Resources |\n102: |-------|--------|-------------------|\n103: | Init | No JSONL exists or setup context | `loop_protocol.md`, `state_format.md`, `state_jsonl.md` |\n104: | Iteration | Dispatch context includes iteration number | `loop_protocol.md`, `state_outputs.md`, `convergence_signals.md` |\n105: | Stuck | Dispatch context includes recovery language | `convergence_recovery.md`, `state_reducer_registry.md` |\n106: | Synthesis | STOP candidate or final report | `convergence.md`, `state_outputs.md`, `spec_check_protocol.md` |\n107: \n108: ### Smart Router Pseudocode\n109: \n110: The authoritative routing logic for scoped loading, weighted intent scoring, ambiguity handling, and graceful fallback.\n111: \n112: - Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively scans `references/` and `assets/`.\n113: - Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards paths, checks `inventory`, and suppresses repeats with `seen`.\n114: - Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - intent labels route to loop resource families without static file inventories.\n115: - Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST` requests disambiguation and missing families return a helpful notice.\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: from pathlib import Path\n119: \n120: SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\n121: RESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\n122: DEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/guides/quick_reference.md\"\n123: \n124: INTENT_SIGNALS = {\n125:     \"LOOP_SETUP\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"autoresearch\", \"deep research\", \"research loop\", \"autonomous research\", \"setup\", \"init\"]},\n126:     \"ITERATION\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"iteration\", \"next round\", \"continue research\", \"research cycle\", \"delta\", \"focus\"]},\n127:     \"CONVERGENCE\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"convergence\", \"stop condition\", \"diminishing returns\", \"legal stop\", \"newInfoRatio\"]},\n128:     \"RECOVERY\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"stuck\", \"recovery\", \"timeout\", \"reconstruct\", \"blocked stop\", \"blocked_stop\"]},\n129:     \"STATE\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"state file\", \"jsonl\", \"strategy\", \"dashboard\", \"registry\", \"lineage\"]},\n130:     \"SPEC_ANCHORING\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"spec.md\", \"generated fence\", \"folder_state\", \"lock\", \"spec anchoring\"]},\n131:     \"RUNTIME_PARITY\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"runtime\", \"capability\", \"parity\", \"codex\", \"claude\", \"gemini\"]},\n132:     \"RESOURCE_MAP\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"resource map\", \"resource-map\", \"inventory\", \"coverage gate\"]},\n133: }\n134: \n135: RESOURCE_MAP = {\n136:     \"LOOP_SETUP\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_jsonl.md\", \"references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"],\n137:     \"ITERATION\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\"],\n138:     \"CONVERGENCE\": [\"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_graph.md\"],\n139:     \"RECOVERY\": [\"references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n140:     \"STATE\": [\"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_jsonl.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n141:     \"SPEC_ANCHORING\": [\"references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n142:     \"RUNTIME_PARITY\": [\"references/guides/capability_matrix.md\"],\n143:     \"RESOURCE_MAP\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n144: }\n145: \n146: LOADING_LEVELS = {\n147:     \"ALWAYS\": [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n148:     \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full protocol\", \"all references\", \"complete reference\", \"resume deep research\", \"state log\", \"research/iterations\", \"deltas\", \"overnight research\", \"active lineage\", \"reference-only\", \"optimizer\"],\n149:     \"ON_DEMAND\": [\n150:         \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n151:         \"references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\",\n152:         \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n153:         \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n154:         \"references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md\",\n155:         \"references/convergence/convergence_graph.md\",\n156:         \"references/convergence/convergence_reference_only.md\",\n157:         \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n158:         \"references/state/state_jsonl.md\",\n159:         \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n160:         \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n161:         \"references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n162:     ],\n163: }\n164: \n165: UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n166:     \"Confirm setup vs iteration vs convergence vs state recovery\",\n167:     \"Confirm the target spec folder and research packet\",\n168:     \"Provide the current phase, latest iteration, or failing state file\",\n169:     \"Confirm whether full references or quick routing guidance are needed\",\n170: ]\n171: \n172: def _task_text(task) -> str:\n173:     return \" \".join([\n174:         str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")),\n175:         str(getattr(task, \"query\", \"\")),\n176:         \" \".join(getattr(task, \"keywords\", []) or []),\n177:     ]).lower()\n178: \n179: def _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n180:     resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n181:     resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n182:     if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n183:         raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n184:     return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n185: \n186: def _guard_resource_map(resource_map: dict[str, list[str]]) -> None:\n187:     for intent, resources in resource_map.items():\n188:         for relative_path in resources:\n189:             guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n190:             if guarded.startswith(\"references/\"):\n191:                 tail = guarded.removeprefix(\"references/\")\n192:                 if \"/\" not in tail and \"-\" in Path(tail).stem:\n193:                     raise ValueError(f\"RESOURCE_MAP must target canonical references, not compatibility stubs: {intent} -> {guarded}\")\n194: \n195: def discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n196:     docs = []\n197:     for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n198:         if base.exists():\n199:             docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n200:     return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n201: \n202: def score_intents(task) -> dict[str, float]:\n203:     text = _task_text(task)\n204:     scores = {intent: 0.0 for intent in INTENT_SIGNALS}\n205:     for intent, cfg in INTENT_SIGNALS.items():\n206:         for keyword in cfg[\"keywords\"]:\n207:             if keyword in text:\n208:                 scores[intent] += cfg[\"weight\"]\n209:     return scores\n210: \n211: def select_intents(scores: dict[str, float], ambiguity_delta: float = 1.0, max_intents: int = 2) -> list[str]:\n212:     ranked = sorted(scores.items(), key=lambda item: item[1], reverse=True)\n213:     if not ranked or ranked[0][1] <= 0:\n214:         return [\"LOOP_SETUP\"]\n215:     selected = [ranked[0][0]]\n216:     if len(ranked) > 1 and ranked[1][1] > 0 and (ranked[0][1] - ranked[1][1]) <= ambiguity_delta:\n217:         selected.append(ranked[1][0])\n218:     return selected[:max_intents]\n219: \n220: def route_deep_research_resources(task):\n221:     _guard_resource_map(RESOURCE_MAP)\n222:     _guard_resource_map({\"ALWAYS\": LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"], \"ON_DEMAND\": LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]})\n223:     inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n224:     scores = score_intents(task)\n225:     intents = select_intents(scores)\n226:     loaded = []\n227:     seen = set()\n228: \n229:     def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n230:         guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n231:         if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n232:             load(guarded)\n233:             loaded.append(guarded)\n234:             seen.add(guarded)\n235: \n236:     for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]:\n237:         load_if_available(relative_path)\n238: \n239:     if max(scores.values() or [0]) < 0.5:\n240:         return {\n241:             \"intents\": intents,\n242:             \"intent_scores\": scores,\n243:             \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n244:             \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n245:             \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n246:             \"resources\": loaded,\n247:         }\n248: \n249:     matched_intents = []\n250:     for intent in intents:\n251:         before_count = len(loaded)\n252:         for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n253:             load_if_available(relative_path)\n254:         if len(loaded) > before_count:\n255:             matched_intents.append(intent)\n256: \n257:     text = _task_text(task)\n258:     if any(keyword in text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n259:         for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n260:             load_if_available(relative_path)\n261: \n262:     result = {\"intents\": intents, \"intent_scores\": scores, \"resources\": loaded}\n263:     if not matched_intents:\n264:         result[\"notice\"] = f\"No knowledge base found for intent(s): {', '.join(intents)}\"\n265:     return result\n266: ```\n267: \n268: ---\n269: \n270: ## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n271: \n272: ### Invocation Contract\n273: \n274: This skill is invoked exclusively through `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` or `/deep:start-research-loop:confirm`. The command YAML owns state, dispatch, convergence, and synthesis.\n275: \n276: Never simulate the loop with ad hoc shell dispatch, nested CLI loops, direct `@deep-research` Task dispatch, `/tmp` prompt files, or state outside the resolved local research packet.\n277: \n278: ### Executor Selection Contract\n279: \n280: The YAML workflow owns executor selection. Native `@deep-research` is the default path; CLI executors are routed through the workflow, not through ad hoc shell loops.\n281: \n282: Cross-CLI delegation is possible inside each executor sandbox but discouraged. Do not invoke the same CLI from within itself, and do not assume auth from a parent executor propagates to child CLIs.\n283: \n284: Executor invariants:\n285: \n286: 1. Produce a non-empty iteration markdown file at `{state_paths.iteration_pattern}`.\n287: 2. Append a JSONL delta record to `{state_paths.state_log}` with required fields: `type`, `iteration`, `newInfoRatio`, `status`, and `focus`.\n288: 3. Respect the LEAF-agent constraint: no sub-dispatch, no nested loops, and max 12 tool calls per iteration.\n289: \n290: Failure modes include `iteration_file_missing`, `iteration_file_empty`, `jsonl_not_appended`, `jsonl_missing_fields`, and `jsonl_parse_error`. Three consecutive failures route to stuck recovery.\n291: \n292: ### Lifecycle Contract\n293: \n294: Runtime-supported lifecycle modes:\n295: \n296: | Mode | Meaning |\n297: |------|---------|\n298: | `new` | First run against the spec folder |\n299: | `resume` | Continue the active lineage and append a typed `resumed` JSONL event |\n300: | `restart` | Archive the existing research tree, mint a fresh `sessionId`, increment `generation`, and append a typed `restarted` event |\n301: \n302: Deferred modes are `fork` and `completed-continue`. They are reserved but not runtime-supported.\n303: \n304: ### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\n305: \n306: The live code-graph readiness contract reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`.\n307: \n308: `cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility, but the readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\n309: \n310: ### Resource Map Integration\n311: \n312: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init, deep research promotes it from ad hoc context to canonical packet state.\n313: \n314: - Persist `resource_map_present: true` in `deep-research-config.json`.\n315: - Read the map once during init and summarize it into `deep-research-strategy.md` `Known Context`.\n316: - The snapshot MUST include per-section entry counts across `READMEs`, `Documents`, `Commands`, `Agents`, `Skills`, `Specs`, `Scripts`, `Tests`, `Config`, and `Meta`.\n317: - The snapshot MUST also include a one-line theme summary for each resource-map section so later iterations inherit the map's structure without rereading the entire file.\n318: - Per-iteration prompts surface `resource-map.md` as the exclusion set for previously inventoried files.\n319: - Treat files already listed on the map as known inventory, not as net-new discoveries.\n320: - Only flag files as gaps when they look relevant to the active investigation and are missing from the map.\n321: - Final synthesis cites `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in `research.md` References when the map was present at init.\n322: - Convergence also emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from research delta evidence unless the operator passes `--no-resource-map`.\n323: \n324: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` is absent at init:\n325: \n326: - Persist `resource_map_present: false`.\n327: - Write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`.\n328: - Omit the exclusion-set hint from iteration guidance.\n329: - Continue the loop normally; absence is informational, not a failure.\n330: \n331: ### Architecture: 3-Layer Integration\n332: \n333: `/deep:start-research-loop` owns the YAML workflow, which initializes state, dispatches one LEAF iteration at a time, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `research/research.md`, and saves continuity. The `@deep-research` agent executes only one research cycle per dispatch.\n334: \n335: ### State Packet Location\n336: \n337: The research state packet always lives under the target spec's local `research/` folder. Root-spec targets use `{spec_folder}/research/` directly. Child-phase and sub-phase targets use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`. A `pt-NN` subfolder (`{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-{NN}`) is allocated only when prior content already exists in `research/` for a non-matching target (continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact or matching `pt-NN` packet). This avoids the unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n338: \n339: Example (first run on a child phase): `.../026-graph.../019-system-hardening/001-initial-research/004-desc-regen/` writes to `004-desc-regen/research/` directly.\n340: \n341: Example (subsequent run with prior content for a different target): `004-desc-regen/research/004-desc-regen-pt-02/` (pt-NN allocated as a sibling to the prior content).\n342: \n343: State files include `deep-research-config.json`, `deep-research-state.jsonl`, `deep-research-strategy.md`, `deep-research-findings-registry.json`, `deep-research-dashboard.md`, `.deep-research-pause`, `.deep-research.lock`, `resource-map.md`, `research.md`, and `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n344: \n345: v(next): `deep-research-findings-registry.json` is the canonical registry name for sibling-skill consistency.\n346: \n347: ### Core Innovation: Fresh Context Per Iteration\n348: \n349: Each agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files, not memory. This solves context degradation in long research sessions.\n350: \n351: Adapted from: karpathy/autoresearch (loop concept), AGR (fresh context \"Ralph Loop\"), pi-autoresearch (JSONL state), autoresearch-opencode (context injection).\n352: \n353: ### Data Flow\n354: \n355: Init creates config, strategy, and state logs. Each loop reads state, checks convergence, dispatches `@deep-research`, writes iteration markdown and JSONL deltas, refreshes reducer-owned state, and either continues or synthesizes and saves continuity.\n356: \n357: Late-INIT can also anchor the research run to `spec.md`: the workflow acquires the advisory lock, classifies `folder_state`, seeds or appends bounded context before LOOP, and then syncs one generated findings block back into `spec.md` during SYNTHESIS while keeping `research/research.md` canonical.\n358: \n359: That contract is exact:\n360: - `folder_state` is always one of `no-spec`, `spec-present`, `spec-just-created-by-this-run`, or `conflict-detected`\n361: - the advisory lock lives at `research/.deep-research.lock` from late INIT through save, skip-save, or cancel cleanup\n362: - post-synthesis write-back replaces exactly one `<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->` ... `<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->` fence under the chosen host anchor\n363: - the full bounded mutation rules live in [spec_check_protocol.md](references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md)\n364: \n365: ### Key Concepts\n366: \n367: Research continuity is externalized to files, each iteration starts fresh, convergence uses newInfoRatio/stuck/question signals, strategy and registry are reducer-owned, JSONL remains append-only, and final synthesis consolidates `research/research.md`.\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## 4. RULES\n372: \n373: ### ALWAYS\n374: \n375: 1. **Read state first** -- Agent must read JSONL and strategy.md before any research action\n376:    - Init validates the research charter (Non-Goals + Stop Conditions in `deep-research-strategy.md`, Step 5a): appends empty placeholders if missing, presents the charter for review in confirm mode.\n377: 2. **One focus per iteration** -- Pick ONE research sub-topic from strategy.md \"Next Focus\"\n378: 3. **Externalize findings** -- Write to iteration-NNN.md, not held in agent context\n379: 4. **Update strategy** -- Append to \"What Worked\"/\"What Failed\", update \"Next Focus\"\n380: 5. **Report newInfoRatio** -- Every iteration JSONL record must include newInfoRatio\n381: 6. **Respect exhausted approaches** -- Never retry approaches in the \"Exhausted\" list\n382: 7. **Cite sources** -- Every finding must cite `[SOURCE: url]` or `[SOURCE: file:line]`\n383: 8. **Use generate-context.js for memory saves** -- Never manually create memory files\n384: 9. **Treat research/research.md as workflow-owned** -- Iteration findings feed synthesis; the workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md`\n385: 10. **Document ruled-out directions per iteration** -- Every iteration must include what was tried and failed\n386: 11. **Report newInfoRatio + 1-sentence novelty justification** -- Every JSONL iteration record must include both\n387: 12. **Quality guards must pass before convergence** -- Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single-weak-source checks must pass before STOP can trigger\n388: 13. **Respect reducer ownership** -- The workflow reducer, not the agent, is the source of truth for strategy machine-owned sections, dashboard metrics, and findings registry updates\n389: 14. **Use canonical packet names only** -- Write `deep-research-*` artifacts and `research/.deep-research-pause`; legacy names are read-only migration aliases\n390: 15. **Invoke through the command workflow** -- Use `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` or `/deep:start-research-loop:confirm`, and let the YAML workflow own dispatch\n391: \n392: ### NEVER\n393: \n394: 1. **Dispatch sub-agents** -- @deep-research is LEAF-only (NDP compliance)\n395: 2. **Hold findings in context** -- Write everything to files\n396: 3. **Exceed TCB** -- Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12)\n397: 4. **Ask the user** -- Autonomous execution; make best-judgment decisions\n398: 5. **Skip convergence checks** -- Every iteration must be evaluated\n399: 6. **Modify config after init** -- Config is read-only after initialization\n400: 7. **Overwrite prior findings** -- Append to research/research.md, never replace\n401: 8. **Implement fixes during research** -- Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n402: 9. **Simulate loop dispatch** -- Do not write custom shell loops, nested CLI loops, `/tmp` prompt dispatchers, or direct Task loops for `@deep-research`. **Command-driven fan-out via `step_fanout_spawn` in the YAML is SUPPORTED** — use `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flags on the command; ad-hoc shell fan-out and intra-lineage wave orchestration remain forbidden.\n403: \n404: ### Iteration Status Enum\n405: \n406: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n407: \n408: - `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but important conceptual breakthrough\n409: - `thought`: Analytical-only iteration, no evidence gathering\n410: \n411: ### EXPERIMENTAL / REFERENCE-ONLY FEATURES\n412: \n413: These concepts remain documented for future design work, but they are not part of the live executable contract for `/deep:start-research-loop`:\n414: 1. **Wave orchestration** -- parallel question fan-out and pruning within a single lineage remains reference-only (intra-lineage wave)\n415: 2. **Checkpoint commits** -- per-iteration git commits\n416: 3. **Multi-lineage fan-out** -- SUPPORTED via `--executor`/`--executors` flags on the command (see §8 EXAMPLES). Each lineage is an independent full loop in `{artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/`, converging independently. This is not \"wave orchestration\"; it is N independent loops.\n417: 4. **Alternate CLI dispatch** -- process-isolated `claude -p` or similar dispatch modes are used internally by `fanout-run.cjs`; do not write them ad-hoc from within a research session\n418: \n419: ### ESCALATE IF\n420: \n421: 1. **3+ consecutive timeouts** -- Infrastructure issue, not research problem\n422: 2. **State file corruption unrecoverable** -- Cannot reconstruct from JSONL or iteration files\n423: 3. **All approaches exhausted with questions remaining** -- Research may need human guidance\n424: 4. **Security concern in findings** -- Proprietary code or credentials discovered\n425: 5. **All recovery tiers exhausted** -- No automatic recovery path remaining\n426: \n427: ---\n428: \n429: ## 5. REFERENCES\n430: \n431: Core documentation: `references/guides/quick_reference.md`, `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`, `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`, `references/convergence/convergence.md`, and `references/state/state_format.md`.\n432: \n433: Focused convergence references: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`, and `references/convergence/convergence_reference_only.md`.\n434: \n435: Focused state references: `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`.\n436: \n437: Templates: `assets/deep_research_config.json`, `assets/deep_research_strategy.md`, `assets/deep_research_dashboard.md`, `assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl`, and `assets/runtime_capabilities.json`.\n438: \n439: Cross-skill alignment: `deep-research` owns iterative investigation. Its shared resource family mirrors `deep-review` and `deep-ai-council`, but its vocabulary remains novelty, sources, negative knowledge, question coverage, and research synthesis rather than severity findings or council agreement.\n440: \n441: ---\n442: \n443: ## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n444: \n445: ### Loop Completion\n446: - Research loop ran to convergence or max iterations\n447: - All state files present and consistent (config, JSONL, strategy)\n448: - research/resource-map.md produced from converged deltas unless `config.resource_map.emit == false` (operator flag: `--no-resource-map`)\n449: - research/research.md produced with findings from all iterations\n450: - Canonical continuity surfaces updated via generate-context.js\n451: \n452: ### Quality Gates\n453: \n454: Blocking gates: valid config/strategy/state before loop, iteration markdown plus JSONL plus reducer refresh per iteration, final `research/research.md` and convergence report after loop, and quality guards for source diversity/focus/no weak single source. Continuity save is expected but non-blocking.\n455: \n456: ### Convergence Report\n457: \n458: Every completed loop produces a convergence report:\n459: - Stop reason (converged, max_iterations, all_questions_answered, stuck_unrecoverable)\n460: - Total iterations completed\n461: - Questions answered ratio\n462: - Average newInfoRatio trend\n463: \n464: ---\n465: \n466: ## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n467: \n468: ### Framework Integration\n469: \n470: This skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in the active runtime's root doc (CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, CODEX.md, or GEMINI.md).\n471: \n472: Key integrations:\n473: - **Gate 2**: Skill routing via `skill_advisor.py` (keywords: autoresearch, deep research)\n474: - **Gate 3**: File modifications require spec folder question per the root doc Gate 3\n475: - **Continuity**: `/speckit:resume` is the operator-facing recovery surface; canonical packet continuity is written via `generate-context.js`\n476: - **Orchestrator**: @orchestrate dispatches @deep-research as LEAF agent\n477: \n478: ### Continuity Integration\n479: \n480: Before research, recover context with `/speckit:resume` using `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`. During each iteration, write `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, append JSONL, and let the reducer refresh strategy/registry/dashboard. After research, save continuity through `generate-context.js`.\n481: \n482: ### Command Integration\n483: \n484: | Command | Relationship |\n485: |---------|-------------|\n486: | `/deep:start-research-loop` | Primary invocation point |\n487: | `/speckit:resume` | Canonical recovery surface before resuming or extending an active packet |\n488: | `/speckit:plan` | Next step after deep research completes |\n489: | `/memory:save` | Manual memory save (deep research auto-saves) |\n490: \n491: ---\n492: \n493: ## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n494: \n495: The router discovers reference and markdown asset docs dynamically. Start with `references/guides/quick_reference.md`, then route to loop protocol, spec anchoring, convergence, state, runtime parity, or recovery references based on intent.\n496: \n497: Scripts: `scripts/reduce-state.cjs`, `scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`.\n498: \n499: Related skills: `deep-review` for iterative audit loops, `deep-loop-runtime` for shared executor/state/coverage-graph runtime, and `system-spec-kit` for command-owned state, packet anchoring, and continuity saves.\n\n(End of file - total 499 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: deep-research\ndescription: \"Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation, externalized state, convergence detection, fresh context per pass.\"\nallowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, memory_context, memory_search]\nargument-hint: \"[topic] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N]\"\nversion: 1.13.1.0\n---\n\n<!-- Keywords: autoresearch, deep-research, iterative-research, autonomous-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, research-agent, JSONL-state, strategy-file -->\n\n# Autonomous Deep Research Loop\n\nNote: `Task` is allowed for the command executor that manages the loop. The `@deep-research` agent itself is LEAF-only and does not dispatch sub-agents.\n\nIterative research protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, and convergence detection for deep technical investigation.\n\nRuntime path resolution:\n- OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n- Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n- Codex runtime: `.codex/agents/*.toml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/SKILL.md","text":"---\nname: deep-research\ndescription: \"Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation, externalized state, convergence detection, fresh context per pass.\"\nallowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, memory_context, memory_search]\nargument-hint: \"[topic] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N]\"\nversion: 1.13.1.0\n---\n\n<!-- Keywords: autoresearch, deep-research, iterative-research, autonomous-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, research-agent, JSONL-state, strategy-file -->\n\n# Autonomous Deep Research Loop\n\nNote: `Task` is allowed for the command executor that manages the loop. The `@deep-research` agent itself is LEAF-only and does not dispatch sub-agents.\n\nIterative research protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, and convergence detection for deep technical investigation.\n\nRuntime path resolution:\n- OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n- Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n- Codex runtime: `.codex/agents/*.toml`\n\nOperator contract precedence for this skill surface:\n- Command entrypoint syntax in `.opencode/commands/deep/start-research-loop.md`\n- Convergence math in `references/convergence/convergence.md` and the deep-research YAML workflow\n- Runtime agent inventories from the checked-in runtime directories above\n\n### Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n\n**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n- `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. See this skill's changelog and decision records for the cross-sibling threshold research and parity invariants that confirm thresholds do not carry across siblings.\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### Activation Triggers\n\nUse this skill when:\n- Deep investigation requiring multiple rounds of discovery\n- Topic spans 3+ technical domains or sources\n- Initial findings need progressive refinement\n- Overnight or unattended research sessions\n- Research where prior findings inform subsequent queries\n\nKeyword triggers:\n\n- `autoresearch`\n- `deep research`\n- `autonomous research`\n- `research loop`\n- `iterative research`\n- `multi-round research`\n- `deep investigation`\n- `comprehensive research`\n\n### Use Cases\n\nUse deep-research for multi-round technical investigation, source triangulation, repeated exploration with fresh context, and research sessions where prior findings should shape the next focus.\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- Simple, single-question research (use direct codebase search or `/speckit:plan`)\n- Known-solution documentation (use `/speckit:plan`)\n- Implementation tasks (use `/speckit:implement`)\n- Quick codebase searches (use `@context` or direct Grep/Glob)\n- Fewer than 3 sources needed (single-pass research suffices)\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n> Pattern: aligned with the [sk-doc smart-router resilience template](../sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md).\n\n### Resource Domains\n\nThe router discovers markdown resources recursively from `references/` and `assets/`, then applies intent scoring from `RESOURCE_MAP`. Keep routing domain-focused rather than hardcoding exhaustive inventories.\n\n- `references/guides/quick_reference.md` for the first-touch operator cheat sheet.\n- `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` for lifecycle, dispatch, reducer sequencing, and command-owned state flow.\n- `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` for bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back.\n- `references/convergence*.md` for stop contracts, signals, recovery, graph gates, and reference-only convergence ideas.\n- `references/state*.md` for packet layout, JSONL records, markdown outputs, reducer ownership, and reconstruction.\n- `references/guides/capability_matrix.md` for runtime parity.\n- `assets/*.md` for markdown templates and prompt assets that are safe to route through guarded markdown loading.\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level | When to Load | Resources |\n|-------|--------------|-----------|\n| ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | Quick reference baseline |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Loop, convergence, state, spec anchoring, runtime parity references |\n| ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request | Full reference set and markdown assets |\n\n### Phase Signals\n\n| Phase | Signal | Primary Resources |\n|-------|--------|-------------------|\n| Init | No JSONL exists or setup context | `loop_protocol.md`, `state_format.md`, `state_jsonl.md` |\n| Iteration | Dispatch context includes iteration number | `loop_protocol.md`, `state_outputs.md`, `convergence_signals.md` |\n| Stuck | Dispatch context includes recovery language | `convergence_recovery.md`, `state_reducer_registry.md` |\n| Synthesis | STOP candidate or final report | `convergence.md`, `state_outputs.md`, `spec_check_protocol.md` |\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\nThe authoritative routing logic for scoped loading, weighted intent scoring, ambiguity handling, and graceful fallback.\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively scans `references/` and `assets/`.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards paths, checks `inventory`, and suppresses repeats with `seen`.\n- Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - intent labels route to loop resource families without static file inventories.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST` requests disambiguation and missing families return a helpful notice.\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\nDEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/guides/quick_reference.md\"\n\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"LOOP_SETUP\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"autoresearch\", \"deep research\", \"research loop\", \"autonomous research\", \"setup\", \"init\"]},\n    \"ITERATION\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"iteration\", \"next round\", \"continue research\", \"research cycle\", \"delta\", \"focus\"]},\n    \"CONVERGENCE\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"convergence\", \"stop condition\", \"diminishing returns\", \"legal stop\", \"newInfoRatio\"]},\n    \"RECOVERY\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"stuck\", \"recovery\", \"timeout\", \"reconstruct\", \"blocked stop\", \"blocked_stop\"]},\n    \"STATE\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"state file\", \"jsonl\", \"strategy\", \"dashboard\", \"registry\", \"lineage\"]},\n    \"SPEC_ANCHORING\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"spec.md\", \"generated fence\", \"folder_state\", \"lock\", \"spec anchoring\"]},\n    \"RUNTIME_PARITY\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"runtime\", \"capability\", \"parity\", \"codex\", \"claude\", \"gemini\"]},\n    \"RESOURCE_MAP\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"resource map\", \"resource-map\", \"inventory\", \"coverage gate\"]},\n}\n\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"LOOP_SETUP\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_jsonl.md\", \"references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"],\n    \"ITERATION\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\"],\n    \"CONVERGENCE\": [\"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_graph.md\"],\n    \"RECOVERY\": [\"references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n    \"STATE\": [\"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_jsonl.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n    \"SPEC_ANCHORING\": [\"references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n    \"RUNTIME_PARITY\": [\"references/guides/capability_matrix.md\"],\n    \"RESOURCE_MAP\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\": [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full protocol\", \"all references\", \"complete reference\", \"resume deep research\", \"state log\", \"research/iterations\", \"deltas\", \"overnight research\", \"active lineage\", \"reference-only\", \"optimizer\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\": [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_graph.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_reference_only.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_jsonl.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n        \"references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Confirm setup vs iteration vs convergence vs state recovery\",\n    \"Confirm the target spec folder and research packet\",\n    \"Provide the current phase, latest iteration, or failing state file\",\n    \"Confirm whether full references or quick routing guidance are needed\",\n]\n\ndef _task_text(task) -> str:\n    return \" \".join([\n        str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")),\n        str(getattr(task, \"query\", \"\")),\n        \" \".join(getattr(task, \"keywords\", []) or []),\n    ]).lower()\n\ndef _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n    if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n        raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n\ndef _guard_resource_map(resource_map: dict[str, list[str]]) -> None:\n    for intent, resources in resource_map.items():\n        for relative_path in resources:\n            guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n            if guarded.startswith(\"references/\"):\n                tail = guarded.removeprefix(\"references/\")\n                if \"/\" not in tail and \"-\" in Path(tail).stem:\n                    raise ValueError(f\"RESOURCE_MAP must target canonical references, not compatibility stubs: {intent} -> {guarded}\")\n\ndef discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n    docs = []\n    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n        if base.exists():\n            docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n\ndef score_intents(task) -> dict[str, float]:\n    text = _task_text(task)\n    scores = {intent: 0.0 for intent in INTENT_SIGNALS}\n    for intent, cfg in INTENT_SIGNALS.items():\n        for keyword in cfg[\"keywords\"]:\n            if keyword in text:\n                scores[intent] += cfg[\"weight\"]\n    return scores\n\ndef select_intents(scores: dict[str, float], ambiguity_delta: float = 1.0, max_intents: int = 2) -> list[str]:\n    ranked = sorted(scores.items(), key=lambda item: item[1], reverse=True)\n    if not ranked or ranked[0][1] <= 0:\n        return [\"LOOP_SETUP\"]\n    selected = [ranked[0][0]]\n    if len(ranked) > 1 and ranked[1][1] > 0 and (ranked[0][1] - ranked[1][1]) <= ambiguity_delta:\n        selected.append(ranked[1][0])\n    return selected[:max_intents]\n\ndef route_deep_research_resources(task):\n    _guard_resource_map(RESOURCE_MAP)\n    _guard_resource_map({\"ALWAYS\": LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"], \"ON_DEMAND\": LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]})\n    inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n    scores = score_intents(task)\n    intents = select_intents(scores)\n    loaded = []\n    seen = set()\n\n    def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n        guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n        if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n            load(guarded)\n            loaded.append(guarded)\n            seen.add(guarded)\n\n    for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    if max(scores.values() or [0]) < 0.5:\n        return {\n            \"intents\": intents,\n            \"intent_scores\": scores,\n            \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n            \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n            \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    matched_intents = []\n    for intent in intents:\n        before_count = len(loaded)\n        for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n        if len(loaded) > before_count:\n            matched_intents.append(intent)\n\n    text = _task_text(task)\n    if any(keyword in text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n        for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    result = {\"intents\": intents, \"intent_scores\": scores, \"resources\": loaded}\n    if not matched_intents:\n        result[\"notice\"] = f\"No knowledge base found for intent(s): {', '.join(intents)}\"\n    return result\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Invocation Contract\n\nThis skill is invoked exclusively through `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` or `/deep:start-research-loop:confirm`. The command YAML owns state, dispatch, convergence, and synthesis.\n\nNever simulate the loop with ad hoc shell dispatch, nested CLI loops, direct `@deep-research` Task dispatch, `/tmp` prompt files, or state outside the resolved local research packet.\n\n### Executor Selection Contract\n\nThe YAML workflow owns executor selection. Native `@deep-research` is the default path; CLI executors are routed through the workflow, not through ad hoc shell loops.\n\nCross-CLI delegation is possible inside each executor sandbox but discouraged. Do not invoke the same CLI from within itself, and do not assume auth from a parent executor propagates to child CLIs.\n\nExecutor invariants:\n\n1. Produce a non-empty iteration markdown file at `{state_paths.iteration_pattern}`.\n2. Append a JSONL delta record to `{state_paths.state_log}` with required fields: `type`, `iteration`, `newInfoRatio`, `status`, and `focus`.\n3. Respect the LEAF-agent constraint: no sub-dispatch, no nested loops, and max 12 tool calls per iteration.\n\nFailure modes include `iteration_file_missing`, `iteration_file_empty`, `jsonl_not_appended`, `jsonl_missing_fields`, and `jsonl_parse_error`. Three consecutive failures route to stuck recovery.\n\n### Lifecycle Contract\n\nRuntime-supported lifecycle modes:\n\n| Mode | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `new` | First run against the spec folder |\n| `resume` | Continue the active lineage and append a typed `resumed` JSONL event |\n| `restart` | Archive the existing research tree, mint a fresh `sessionId`, increment `generation`, and append a typed `restarted` event |\n\nDeferred modes are `fork` and `completed-continue`. They are reserved but not runtime-supported.\n\n### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\n\nThe live code-graph readiness contract reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`.\n\n`cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility, but the readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\n\n### Resource Map Integration\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init, deep research promotes it from ad hoc context to canonical packet state.\n\n- Persist `resource_map_present: true` in `deep-research-config.json`.\n- Read the map once during init and summarize it into `deep-research-strategy.md` `Known Context`.\n- The snapshot MUST include per-section entry counts across `READMEs`, `Documents`, `Commands`, `Agents`, `Skills`, `Specs`, `Scripts`, `Tests`, `Config`, and `Meta`.\n- The snapshot MUST also include a one-line theme summary for each resource-map section so later iterations inherit the map's structure without rereading the entire file.\n- Per-iteration prompts surface `resource-map.md` as the exclusion set for previously inventoried files.\n- Treat files already listed on the map as known inventory, not as net-new discoveries.\n- Only flag files as gaps when they look relevant to the active investigation and are missing from the map.\n- Final synthesis cites `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in `research.md` References when the map was present at init.\n- Convergence also emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from research delta evidence unless the operator passes `--no-resource-map`.\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` is absent at init:\n\n- Persist `resource_map_present: false`.\n- Write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`.\n- Omit the exclusion-set hint from iteration guidance.\n- Continue the loop normally; absence is informational, not a failure.\n\n### Architecture: 3-Layer Integration\n\n`/deep:start-research-loop` owns the YAML workflow, which initializes state, dispatches one LEAF iteration at a time, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `research/research.md`, and saves continuity. The `@deep-research` agent executes only one research cycle per dispatch.\n\n### State Packet Location\n\nThe research state packet always lives under the target spec's local `research/` folder. Root-spec targets use `{spec_folder}/research/` directly. Child-phase and sub-phase targets use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`. A `pt-NN` subfolder (`{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-{NN}`) is allocated only when prior content already exists in `research/` for a non-matching target (continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact or matching `pt-NN` packet). This avoids the unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n\nExample (first run on a child phase): `.../026-graph.../019-system-hardening/001-initial-research/004-desc-regen/` writes to `004-desc-regen/research/` directly.\n\nExample (subsequent run with prior content for a different target): `004-desc-regen/research/004-desc-regen-pt-02/` (pt-NN allocated as a sibling to the prior content).\n\nState files include `deep-research-config.json`, `deep-research-state.jsonl`, `deep-research-strategy.md`, `deep-research-findings-registry.json`, `deep-research-dashboard.md`, `.deep-research-pause`, `.deep-research.lock`, `resource-map.md`, `research.md`, and `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n\nv(next): `deep-research-findings-registry.json` is the canonical registry name for sibling-skill consistency.\n\n### Core Innovation: Fresh Context Per Iteration\n\nEach agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files, not memory. This solves context degradation in long research sessions.\n\nAdapted from: karpathy/autoresearch (loop concept), AGR (fresh context \"Ralph Loop\"), pi-autoresearch (JSONL state), autoresearch-opencode (context injection).\n\n### Data Flow\n\nInit creates config, strategy, and state logs. Each loop reads state, checks convergence, dispatches `@deep-research`, writes iteration markdown and JSONL deltas, refreshes reducer-owned state, and either continues or synthesizes and saves continuity.\n\nLate-INIT can also anchor the research run to `spec.md`: the workflow acquires the advisory lock, classifies `folder_state`, seeds or appends bounded context before LOOP, and then syncs one generated findings block back into `spec.md` during SYNTHESIS while keeping `research/research.md` canonical.\n\nThat contract is exact:\n- `folder_state` is always one of `no-spec`, `spec-present`, `spec-just-created-by-this-run`, or `conflict-detected`\n- the advisory lock lives at `research/.deep-research.lock` from late INIT through save, skip-save, or cancel cleanup\n- post-synthesis write-back replaces exactly one `<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->` ... `<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->` fence under the chosen host anchor\n- the full bounded mutation rules live in [spec_check_protocol.md](references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md)\n\n### Key Concepts\n\nResearch continuity is externalized to files, each iteration starts fresh, convergence uses newInfoRatio/stuck/question signals, strategy and registry are reducer-owned, JSONL remains append-only, and final synthesis consolidates `research/research.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n1. **Read state first** -- Agent must read JSONL and strategy.md before any research action\n   - Init validates the research charter (Non-Goals + Stop Conditions in `deep-research-strategy.md`, Step 5a): appends empty placeholders if missing, presents the charter for review in confirm mode.\n2. **One focus per iteration** -- Pick ONE research sub-topic from strategy.md \"Next Focus\"\n3. **Externalize findings** -- Write to iteration-NNN.md, not held in agent context\n4. **Update strategy** -- Append to \"What Worked\"/\"What Failed\", update \"Next Focus\"\n5. **Report newInfoRatio** -- Every iteration JSONL record must include newInfoRatio\n6. **Respect exhausted approaches** -- Never retry approaches in the \"Exhausted\" list\n7. **Cite sources** -- Every finding must cite `[SOURCE: url]` or `[SOURCE: file:line]`\n8. **Use generate-context.js for memory saves** -- Never manually create memory files\n9. **Treat research/research.md as workflow-owned** -- Iteration findings feed synthesis; the workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md`\n10. **Document ruled-out directions per iteration** -- Every iteration must include what was tried and failed\n11. **Report newInfoRatio + 1-sentence novelty justification** -- Every JSONL iteration record must include both\n12. **Quality guards must pass before convergence** -- Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single-weak-source checks must pass before STOP can trigger\n13. **Respect reducer ownership** -- The workflow reducer, not the agent, is the source of truth for strategy machine-owned sections, dashboard metrics, and findings registry updates\n14. **Use canonical packet names only** -- Write `deep-research-*` artifacts and `research/.deep-research-pause`; legacy names are read-only migration aliases\n15. **Invoke through the command workflow** -- Use `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` or `/deep:start-research-loop:confirm`, and let the YAML workflow own dispatch\n\n### NEVER\n\n1. **Dispatch sub-agents** -- @deep-research is LEAF-only (NDP compliance)\n2. **Hold findings in context** -- Write everything to files\n3. **Exceed TCB** -- Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12)\n4. **Ask the user** -- Autonomous execution; make best-judgment decisions\n5. **Skip convergence checks** -- Every iteration must be evaluated\n6. **Modify config after init** -- Config is read-only after initialization\n7. **Overwrite prior findings** -- Append to research/research.md, never replace\n8. **Implement fixes during research** -- Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n9. **Simulate loop dispatch** -- Do not write custom shell loops, nested CLI loops, `/tmp` prompt dispatchers, or direct Task loops for `@deep-research`. **Command-driven fan-out via `step_fanout_spawn` in the YAML is SUPPORTED** — use `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flags on the command; ad-hoc shell fan-out and intra-lineage wave orchestration remain forbidden.\n\n### Iteration Status Enum\n\n`complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n\n- `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but important conceptual breakthrough\n- `thought`: Analytical-only iteration, no evidence gathering\n\n### EXPERIMENTAL / REFERENCE-ONLY FEATURES\n\nThese concepts remain documented for future design work, but they are not part of the live executable contract for `/deep:start-research-loop`:\n1. **Wave orchestration** -- parallel question fan-out and pruning within a single lineage remains reference-only (intra-lineage wave)\n2. **Checkpoint commits** -- per-iteration git commits\n3. **Multi-lineage fan-out** -- SUPPORTED via `--executor`/`--executors` flags on the command (see §8 EXAMPLES). Each lineage is an independent full loop in `{artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/`, converging independently. This is not \"wave orchestration\"; it is N independent loops.\n4. **Alternate CLI dispatch** -- process-isolated `claude -p` or similar dispatch modes are used internally by `fanout-run.cjs`; do not write them ad-hoc from within a research session\n\n### ESCALATE IF\n\n1. **3+ consecutive timeouts** -- Infrastructure issue, not research problem\n2. **State file corruption unrecoverable** -- Cannot reconstruct from JSONL or iteration files\n3. **All approaches exhausted with questions remaining** -- Research may need human guidance\n4. **Security concern in findings** -- Proprietary code or credentials discovered\n5. **All recovery tiers exhausted** -- No automatic recovery path remaining\n\n---\n\n## 5. REFERENCES\n\nCore documentation: `references/guides/quick_reference.md`, `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`, `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`, `references/convergence/convergence.md`, and `references/state/state_format.md`.\n\nFocused convergence references: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`, and `references/convergence/convergence_reference_only.md`.\n\nFocused state references: `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\nTemplates: `assets/deep_research_config.json`, `assets/deep_research_strategy.md`, `assets/deep_research_dashboard.md`, `assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl`, and `assets/runtime_capabilities.json`.\n\nCross-skill alignment: `deep-research` owns iterative investigation. Its shared resource family mirrors `deep-review` and `deep-ai-council`, but its vocabulary remains novelty, sources, negative knowledge, question coverage, and research synthesis rather than severity findings or council agreement.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Loop Completion\n- Research loop ran to convergence or max iterations\n- All state files present and consistent (config, JSONL, strategy)\n- research/resource-map.md produced from converged deltas unless `config.resource_map.emit == false` (operator flag: `--no-resource-map`)\n- research/research.md produced with findings from all iterations\n- Canonical continuity surfaces updated via generate-context.js\n\n### Quality Gates\n\nBlocking gates: valid config/strategy/state before loop, iteration markdown plus JSONL plus reducer refresh per iteration, final `research/research.md` and convergence report after loop, and quality guards for source diversity/focus/no weak single source. Continuity save is expected but non-blocking.\n\n### Convergence Report\n\nEvery completed loop produces a convergence report:\n- Stop reason (converged, max_iterations, all_questions_answered, stuck_unrecoverable)\n- Total iterations completed\n- Questions answered ratio\n- Average newInfoRatio trend\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n### Framework Integration\n\nThis skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in the active runtime's root doc (CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, CODEX.md, or GEMINI.md).\n\nKey integrations:\n- **Gate 2**: Skill routing via `skill_advisor.py` (keywords: autoresearch, deep research)\n- **Gate 3**: File modifications require spec folder question per the root doc Gate 3\n- **Continuity**: `/speckit:resume` is the operator-facing recovery surface; canonical packet continuity is written via `generate-context.js`\n- **Orchestrator**: @orchestrate dispatches @deep-research as LEAF agent\n\n### Continuity Integration\n\nBefore research, recover context with `/speckit:resume` using `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`. During each iteration, write `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, append JSONL, and let the reducer refresh strategy/registry/dashboard. After research, save continuity through `generate-context.js`.\n\n### Command Integration\n\n| Command | Relationship |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `/deep:start-research-loop` | Primary invocation point |\n| `/speckit:resume` | Canonical recovery surface before resuming or extending an active packet |\n| `/speckit:plan` | Next step after deep research completes |\n| `/memory:save` | Manual memory save (deep research auto-saves) |\n\n---\n\n## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nThe router discovers reference and markdown asset docs dynamically. Start with `references/guides/quick_reference.md`, then route to loop protocol, spec anchoring, convergence, state, runtime parity, or recovery references based on intent.\n\nScripts: `scripts/reduce-state.cjs`, `scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`.\n\nRelated skills: `deep-review` for iterative audit loops, `deep-loop-runtime` for shared executor/state/coverage-graph runtime, and `system-spec-kit` for command-owned state, packet anchoring, and continuity saves.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":499,"totalLines":499,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1780735936606,"end":1780735936618}},"id":"prt_e9c2205e7001RPY1BiOxjBkRcd","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c21eabc001M8dM0IAEcrr8aI"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735937565,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_V0lA8gVzkwxL7CMZHjZf8890","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\ndescription.json\ngraph-metadata.json\nimplementation-summary.md\nplan.md\nresearch/\nspec.md\ntasks.md\n\n(7 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"description.json\ngraph-metadata.json\nimplementation-summary.md\nplan.md\nresearch/\nspec.md\ntasks.md","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility","entries":["description.json","graph-metadata.json","implementation-summary.md","plan.md","research/","spec.md","tasks.md"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":7,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility","time":{"start":1780735937553,"end":1780735937560}},"id":"prt_e9c2208e000181e53EkbsblecS","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c21eabc001M8dM0IAEcrr8aI"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780735937830,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"id":"prt_e9c220d23001BzrGIW7BttYkVN","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f99f735171c64f07bf9ef2ccd9597b2a4e2ae6d8","messageID":"msg_e9c21eabc001M8dM0IAEcrr8aI","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":36279,"input":25988,"output":144,"reasoning":35,"cache":{"write":0,"read":10112}},"cost":0.011497166}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780735939250,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"id":"prt_e9c2212ae001HdI5iKR9GGNkc2","messageID":"msg_e9c220e13001CizcxDAsggJ3Ev","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","snapshot":"f99f735171c64f07bf9ef2ccd9597b2a4e2ae6d8","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735946728,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_vCUtECOG9zPahs6j1PuA7787","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Feature Specification: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility [system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/spec]\"\n3: description: \"Deep-research feasibility study: can the mk-spec-memory MCP (37 tools) be replaced by a CLI tool with zero feature loss? Three candidate architectures evaluated by a 3-model fan-out.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"memory mcp cli feasibility\"\n6:   - \"mcp to cli\"\n7:   - \"zero feature loss\"\n8:   - \"mk-spec-memory cli\"\n9:   - \"replace mcp with cli\"\n10: importance_tier: \"important\"\n11: contextType: \"specification\"\n12: _memory:\n13:   continuity:\n14:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"\n15:     last_updated_at: \"2026-06-06T12:30:00Z\"\n16:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n17:     recent_action: \"Bootstrapped the 028 feasibility packet\"\n18:     next_safe_action: \"Launch the 3-lane deep-research fan-out loop\"\n19:     blockers: []\n20:     key_files:\n21:       - \"spec.md\"\n22:       - \"plan.md\"\n23:     completion_pct: 0\n24:     open_questions:\n25:       - \"Which architecture (pure CLI / CLI-over-daemon / hybrid) survives the zero-feature-loss bar?\"\n26:     answered_questions: []\n27: ---\n28: # Feature Specification: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility\n29: \n30: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 1 -->\n31: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core | v2.2 -->\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: <!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n36: ## 1. METADATA\n37: \n38: | Field | Value |\n39: |-------|-------|\n40: | **Level** | 1 |\n41: | **Priority** | P1 |\n42: | **Status** | In Progress |\n43: | **Created** | 2026-06-06 |\n44: | **Branch** | `028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility` |\n45: <!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: <!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n50: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n51: \n52: ### Problem Statement\n53: The mk-spec-memory MCP server (37 tools) is the spec-kit's continuity backbone, but the MCP transport carries real operational costs: a mid-session disconnect on 2026-06-06 permanently removed 45 tools from a live session because Claude Code never reconnects MCP transports, every session pays tool-schema token overhead, and each runtime needs separate MCP registration. Whether a CLI tool could replace the MCP surface WITHOUT losing any feature is unknown.\n54: \n55: ### Purpose\n56: A verdict-shaped deep-research report that settles feasibility: a complete feature-parity matrix, a per-architecture loss table, and a go/no-go recommendation for replacing the MCP with a CLI.\n57: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n62: ## 3. SCOPE\n63: \n64: ### In Scope\n65: - One heterogeneous deep-research fan-out run: DeepSeek-v4-pro, MiniMax-M3, and MiMo-V2.5-Pro lanes via cli-opencode, 5 iterations per lane (terminal cap), concurrency 2.\n66: - Evaluation of THREE candidate architectures against the zero-feature-loss bar: (a) pure per-invocation CLI with no background processes; (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket, killing only the MCP protocol layer; (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand.\n67: - Verdict synthesis in `research/research.md`: 37-tool parity matrix, daemon-dependency loss table, MCP-affordance replacement design, integration-surface migration map, risk register, go/no-go.\n68: \n69: ### Research Key Questions\n70: - **KQ1 — Parity matrix, all 37 tools.** A CLI equivalent per tool. Prior art: `generate-context.js` already performs memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs exist under `scripts/dist/memory/`.\n71: - **KQ2 — Daemon-dependency audit.** What dies per architecture: warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async embedding retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs.\n72: - **KQ3 — MCP-only affordances and replacements.** Tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable semantics plus session-proxy replay classification.\n73: - **KQ4 — Integration-surface migration.** Runtime hooks (Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot) calling `session_bootstrap`/`memory_context`; agents' allowed-tools; `/doctor` flows; deep-loop allowed-tools.\n74: - **KQ5 — Architecture comparison.** Architectures a/b/c scored with effort estimates, a risk register, and a go/no-go recommendation.\n75: \n76: ### Out of Scope\n77: - Any implementation - no CLI is built, no code or config changes to mk-spec-memory, no migration; implementation is a future packet gated on this verdict.\n78: - Benchmark execution - latency or RSS measurements may be proposed by the research, not run by it.\n79: \n80: ### Files to Change\n81: \n82: | File Path | Change Type | Description |\n83: |-----------|-------------|-------------|\n84: | research/** | Create | Workflow-owned deep-research outputs (lineages, registries, research.md) |\n85: | spec.md | Modify | Generated spec-findings fence appended by the workflow at synthesis |\n86: | tasks.md, implementation-summary.md | Modify | Post-run reconciliation |\n87: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: <!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n92: ## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n93: \n94: ### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)\n95: \n96: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n97: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n98: | REQ-001 | All three lanes complete (or salvaged partials are documented) and results merge | `research/orchestration-summary.json` records succeeded lanes; merged `deep-research-findings-registry.json` + `fanout-attribution.md` exist |\n99: | REQ-002 | `research/research.md` is verdict-shaped | Contains a complete 37-row tool parity matrix, a per-architecture (a/b/c) daemon-dependency loss table, and a go/no-go recommendation with risk register and effort estimates, anchored in file:line evidence |\n100: \n101: ### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)\n102: \n103: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n104: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n105: | REQ-003 | Zero-feature-loss bar applied honestly | Every feature is classed ported/adapted/lost per architecture; no unclassified features; \"lost\" entries enumerated explicitly |\n106: <!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n111: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n112: \n113: - **SC-001**: A defensible go/no-go answer to \"can the MCP be dropped without losing features\", with the winning architecture named.\n114: - **SC-002**: Parity coverage spans all 37 tools plus daemon services plus MCP-protocol affordances.\n115: - **SC-003**: Per-lane iteration state recorded (terminal cap 5 x 3 lanes); any lane that legally stopped early is documented with its stop reason.\n116: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: <!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n121: ## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n122: \n123: | Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n124: |------|------|--------|------------|\n125: | Dependency | opencode CLI + three provider pools (deepseek-api, minimax-token-plan, xiaomi-token-plan) | Lane fails mid-run | Salvage sweep recovers partials; merge tolerates partial lineages; single-executor re-run path documented in plan.md |\n126: | Risk | A lane converges before iteration 5 (composite vote) | Med | Broad KQs resist saturation; actual per-lane counts recorded at reconciliation |\n127: | Risk | MiniMax-M3 lane hits the 4h hard cap | Low | 1500s per-iteration ceiling; salvage sweep recovers completed iterations |\n128: | Risk | Research drifts into implementation | Low | Explicit non-goals; lanes are read-only investigators |\n129: <!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n134: ## 7. OPEN QUESTIONS\n135: \n136: - Which of the three architectures survives the zero-feature-loss bar, and at what effort?\n137: - Is strict zero loss achievable at all, or does every path lose something MCP-specific (discovery, permissioning) that must be re-designed rather than ported?\n138: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n\n(End of file - total 138 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Feature Specification: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility [system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/spec]\"\ndescription: \"Deep-research feasibility study: can the mk-spec-memory MCP (37 tools) be replaced by a CLI tool with zero feature loss? Three candidate architectures evaluated by a 3-model fan-out.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"memory mcp cli feasibility\"\n  - \"mcp to cli\"\n  - \"zero feature loss\"\n  - \"mk-spec-memory cli\"\n  - \"replace mcp with cli\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"specification\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-06T12:30:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n    recent_action: \"Bootstrapped the 028 feasibility packet\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Launch the 3-lane deep-research fan-out loop\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files:","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/spec.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Feature Specification: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility [system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/spec]\"\ndescription: \"Deep-research feasibility study: can the mk-spec-memory MCP (37 tools) be replaced by a CLI tool with zero feature loss? Three candidate architectures evaluated by a 3-model fan-out.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"memory mcp cli feasibility\"\n  - \"mcp to cli\"\n  - \"zero feature loss\"\n  - \"mk-spec-memory cli\"\n  - \"replace mcp with cli\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"specification\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-06T12:30:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n    recent_action: \"Bootstrapped the 028 feasibility packet\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Launch the 3-lane deep-research fan-out loop\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files:\n      - \"spec.md\"\n      - \"plan.md\"\n    completion_pct: 0\n    open_questions:\n      - \"Which architecture (pure CLI / CLI-over-daemon / hybrid) survives the zero-feature-loss bar?\"\n    answered_questions: []\n---\n# Feature Specification: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 1 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: spec-core | v2.2 -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n## 1. METADATA\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Level** | 1 |\n| **Priority** | P1 |\n| **Status** | In Progress |\n| **Created** | 2026-06-06 |\n| **Branch** | `028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility` |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\nThe mk-spec-memory MCP server (37 tools) is the spec-kit's continuity backbone, but the MCP transport carries real operational costs: a mid-session disconnect on 2026-06-06 permanently removed 45 tools from a live session because Claude Code never reconnects MCP transports, every session pays tool-schema token overhead, and each runtime needs separate MCP registration. Whether a CLI tool could replace the MCP surface WITHOUT losing any feature is unknown.\n\n### Purpose\nA verdict-shaped deep-research report that settles feasibility: a complete feature-parity matrix, a per-architecture loss table, and a go/no-go recommendation for replacing the MCP with a CLI.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- One heterogeneous deep-research fan-out run: DeepSeek-v4-pro, MiniMax-M3, and MiMo-V2.5-Pro lanes via cli-opencode, 5 iterations per lane (terminal cap), concurrency 2.\n- Evaluation of THREE candidate architectures against the zero-feature-loss bar: (a) pure per-invocation CLI with no background processes; (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket, killing only the MCP protocol layer; (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand.\n- Verdict synthesis in `research/research.md`: 37-tool parity matrix, daemon-dependency loss table, MCP-affordance replacement design, integration-surface migration map, risk register, go/no-go.\n\n### Research Key Questions\n- **KQ1 — Parity matrix, all 37 tools.** A CLI equivalent per tool. Prior art: `generate-context.js` already performs memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs exist under `scripts/dist/memory/`.\n- **KQ2 — Daemon-dependency audit.** What dies per architecture: warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async embedding retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs.\n- **KQ3 — MCP-only affordances and replacements.** Tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable semantics plus session-proxy replay classification.\n- **KQ4 — Integration-surface migration.** Runtime hooks (Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot) calling `session_bootstrap`/`memory_context`; agents' allowed-tools; `/doctor` flows; deep-loop allowed-tools.\n- **KQ5 — Architecture comparison.** Architectures a/b/c scored with effort estimates, a risk register, and a go/no-go recommendation.\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Any implementation - no CLI is built, no code or config changes to mk-spec-memory, no migration; implementation is a future packet gated on this verdict.\n- Benchmark execution - latency or RSS measurements may be proposed by the research, not run by it.\n\n### Files to Change\n\n| File Path | Change Type | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|-------------|\n| research/** | Create | Workflow-owned deep-research outputs (lineages, registries, research.md) |\n| spec.md | Modify | Generated spec-findings fence appended by the workflow at synthesis |\n| tasks.md, implementation-summary.md | Modify | Post-run reconciliation |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n\n### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-001 | All three lanes complete (or salvaged partials are documented) and results merge | `research/orchestration-summary.json` records succeeded lanes; merged `deep-research-findings-registry.json` + `fanout-attribution.md` exist |\n| REQ-002 | `research/research.md` is verdict-shaped | Contains a complete 37-row tool parity matrix, a per-architecture (a/b/c) daemon-dependency loss table, and a go/no-go recommendation with risk register and effort estimates, anchored in file:line evidence |\n\n### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-003 | Zero-feature-loss bar applied honestly | Every feature is classed ported/adapted/lost per architecture; no unclassified features; \"lost\" entries enumerated explicitly |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- **SC-001**: A defensible go/no-go answer to \"can the MCP be dropped without losing features\", with the winning architecture named.\n- **SC-002**: Parity coverage spans all 37 tools plus daemon services plus MCP-protocol affordances.\n- **SC-003**: Per-lane iteration state recorded (terminal cap 5 x 3 lanes); any lane that legally stopped early is documented with its stop reason.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------|--------|------------|\n| Dependency | opencode CLI + three provider pools (deepseek-api, minimax-token-plan, xiaomi-token-plan) | Lane fails mid-run | Salvage sweep recovers partials; merge tolerates partial lineages; single-executor re-run path documented in plan.md |\n| Risk | A lane converges before iteration 5 (composite vote) | Med | Broad KQs resist saturation; actual per-lane counts recorded at reconciliation |\n| Risk | MiniMax-M3 lane hits the 4h hard cap | Low | 1500s per-iteration ceiling; salvage sweep recovers completed iterations |\n| Risk | Research drifts into implementation | Low | Explicit non-goals; lanes are read-only investigators |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n## 7. OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- Which of the three architectures survives the zero-feature-loss bar, and at what effort?\n- Is strict zero loss achievable at all, or does every path lose something MCP-specific (discovery, permissioning) that must be re-designed rather than ported?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":138,"totalLines":138,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/spec.md","time":{"start":1780735946715,"end":1780735946726}},"id":"prt_e9c222c93001CCwq1FVSbB7Bh3","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c220e13001CizcxDAsggJ3Ev"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735947496,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_FTSuKoQUhuZb2PRAmJZm2628","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\n.deep-research.lock\ndeep-research-config.json\ndeep-research-state.jsonl\ndeep-research-strategy.md\nlineages/\norchestration-status.log\n\n(6 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":".deep-research.lock\ndeep-research-config.json\ndeep-research-state.jsonl\ndeep-research-strategy.md\nlineages/\norchestration-status.log","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research","entries":[".deep-research.lock","deep-research-config.json","deep-research-state.jsonl","deep-research-strategy.md","lineages/","orchestration-status.log"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":6,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research","time":{"start":1780735947490,"end":1780735947494}},"id":"prt_e9c223068001UyPZrDzPBzBqb5","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c220e13001CizcxDAsggJ3Ev"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735948300,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_Rt1vcI8gmW44jAVE0GSS3695","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Quick Reference\n3: description: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Research Quick Reference\n7: \n8: One-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n13: \n14: Lookup surface during runs covering when to invoke the loop, what each phase produces, how convergence is computed, and where live state lives on disk. Defer to the full protocol and convergence references for deep reasoning.\n15: \n16: Operator contract source of truth for this page:\n17: - command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/start-research-loop.md`\n18: - convergence stop contract: `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, and the deep-research YAML workflow\n19: - state packet contract: `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## 2. COMMANDS\n24: \n25: | Command | Description |\n26: |---------|-------------|\n27: | `/deep:start-research-loop:auto \"topic\"` | Run autonomous deep research (no approval gates) |\n28: | `/deep:start-research-loop:confirm \"topic\"` | Run with approval gates at each iteration |\n29: | `/deep:start-research-loop \"topic\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n30: \n31: ### Parameters\n32: \n33: | Parameter | Default | Description |\n34: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n35: | `--max-iterations` | 10 | Maximum loop iterations |\n36: | `--convergence` | 0.05 | Stop when avg newInfoRatio below this |\n37: | `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n38: | `progressiveSynthesis` | true | Allow incremental `research/research.md` updates before final synthesis |\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## 3. WHEN TO USE\n43: \n44: | Scenario | Use |\n45: |----------|-----|\n46: | Deep unknown topic, multi-round needed | `/deep:start-research-loop` |\n47: | Simple question, 1-2 sources | Direct search with `@context` |\n48: | Check prior work only | `memory_context()` |\n49: | Exhaustive critical research | `/deep:start-research-loop --max-iterations 15 --convergence 0.02` |\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 4. ARCHITECTURE\n54: \n55: ```text\n56: /deep:start-research-loop  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-research agent (LEAF)\n57:     |                    |                      |\n58:     |                    |                      +-- Read state\n59:     |                    |                      +-- Research (3-5 actions)\n60:     |                    |                      +-- Write findings\n61:     |                    |                      +-- Update state\n62:     |                    |\n63:     |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n64:     |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n65:     |                    +-- Synthesize (final research/research.md)\n66:     |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n67: ```\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## 5. STATE FILES\n72: \n73: | File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n74: |------|----------|--------|---------|\n75: | Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters |\n76: | State | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n77: | Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | What worked/failed, next focus |\n78: | Registry | `research/findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned open/resolved questions and key findings |\n79: | Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Reducer-owned lifecycle and convergence summary |\n80: | Iterations | `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings |\n81: | Output | `research/research.md` | Markdown | Workflow-owned progressive synthesis output |\n82: \n83: > **Live lifecycle branches:** `resume`, `restart`. (`fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not runtime-wired.) `progressiveSynthesis` defaults to `true`, so `research/research.md` is updated during the loop and finalized at synthesis.\n84: \n85: > **Path contract:** root-spec runs write directly to `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase first runs use the local `{spec_folder}/research/` directory directly, with `{ownerSlug}-pt-NN` allocated only when prior non-matching content already exists.\n86: \n87: > **Canonical pause sentinel:** `research/.deep-research-pause`\n88: \n89: > **Runtime capability matrix:** `.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md` and `.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 6. ITERATION STATUS LEGEND\n94: \n95: | Status | Meaning |\n96: |--------|---------|\n97: | `complete` | Normal iteration with findings |\n98: | `timeout` | Exceeded time/tool budget |\n99: | `error` | Failed to produce outputs |\n100: | `stuck` | No new information found |\n101: | `insight` | Low ratio but conceptual breakthrough |\n102: | `thought` | Analytical-only, no evidence |\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## 7. CONVERGENCE DECISION TREE\n107: \n108: ```text\n109: Max iterations reached?\n110:   Yes --> STOP\n111: \n112: All questions answered?\n113:   Yes --> STOP\n114: \n115: stuckThreshold consecutive no-progress?\n116:   Yes --> STUCK_RECOVERY\n117:     Recovery works? --> CONTINUE\n118:     Recovery fails? --> STOP (with gaps)\n119: \n120: Composite convergence (3-signal weighted > 0.60)?\n121:   Yes --> STOP (converged)\n122: \n123: Otherwise --> CONTINUE\n124: ```\n125: \n126: ### 3-Signal Convergence Model\n127: \n128: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Votes STOP When |\n129: |--------|--------|---------------|-----------------|\n130: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | 3 | avg(last 3 newInfoRatios) < convergenceThreshold |\n131: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.35 | 4 | latest ratio <= MAD * 1.4826 |\n132: | Question Entropy | 0.35 | 1 | answered / total questions >= 0.85 |\n133: \n134: **Composite stop threshold:** 0.60 -- weighted stop score must exceed this before quality guards are evaluated.\n135: \n136: Quality guards (source diversity, focus alignment, no single-weak-source) must pass before STOP.\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ## 8. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n141: \n142: Each @deep-research iteration:\n143: 1. Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` and `deep-research-strategy.md`\n144: 2. Determine focus from reducer-owned strategy \"Next Focus\"\n145: 3. Execute 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n146: 4. Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with findings\n147: 5. Append iteration record to `deep-research-state.jsonl`\n148: 6. Let the workflow reducer update `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n149: 7. Optionally update machine-owned sections in `research/research.md` when progressive synthesis is enabled\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## 9. TUNING GUIDE\n154: \n155: | Goal | Adjustment |\n156: |------|------------|\n157: | Deeper research | Lower convergence (0.02), raise max iterations (15) |\n158: | Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.10), lower max iterations (5) |\n159: | Broader coverage | Start with broad topic, let iterations narrow |\n160: | Specific answer | Start with specific question, lower max iterations (5) |\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ## 10. TROUBLESHOOTING\n165: \n166: | Problem | Fix |\n167: |---------|-----|\n168: | Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.05 to 0.02 |\n169: | Repeats same research | Check strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\" is being read |\n170: | Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n171: | State file corrupt | Validate JSONL: `cat research/deep-research-state.jsonl \\| jq .` |\n172: | Loop runs too long | Set lower `--max-iterations` or higher `--convergence` |\n173: \n174: ---\n175: \n176: ## 11. PROGRESS VISUALIZATION\n177: \n178: After each iteration, the orchestrator can display a text-based convergence summary:\n179: \n180: ### Format\n181: \n182: | Element | Format | Example |\n183: |---------|--------|---------|\n184: | newInfoRatio trend | ASCII sparkline | `[0.9 0.7 0.5 0.3 0.1]` |\n185: | Question coverage | Progress bar | `[=======>...] 7/10 (70%)` |\n186: | Composite score | Threshold bar | `[####----] 0.42 / 0.60` |\n187: | Noise floor | Comparison | `ratio: 0.12 > floor: 0.08` |\n188: \n189: ### Example Output\n190: \n191: ```text\n192: ITERATION 5 PROGRESS\n193: ─────────────────────\n194: newInfoRatio: 0.9 -> 0.7 -> 0.5 -> 0.3 -> 0.1  trending down\n195: Questions:   [========>..] 8/10 answered (80%)\n196: Composite:   [######--] 0.48 / 0.60 threshold\n197: Noise floor: 0.08 (ratio 0.10 ABOVE floor)\n198: Stuck count: 0 | Segment: 1 | Recovery: none\n199: Signals: RollingAvg=STOP MAD=CONTINUE Entropy=CONTINUE\n200: ```\n201: \n202: ### When to Display\n203: \n204: - After each iteration evaluation (Step 4)\n205: - In the convergence report (synthesis phase)\n206: - In confirm mode approval gates\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ## 12. RELATED\n211: \n212: | Resource | Purpose |\n213: |----------|---------|\n214: | `@context` | Single-pass codebase search (not iterative) |\n215: | `@orchestrate` | Multi-agent coordination |\n216: | `memory_context()` | Prior work retrieval |\n217: | `generate-context.js` | Supported memory save script |\n218: | `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` | Convergence signal details |\n219: | `references/state/state_jsonl.md` | JSONL state record details |\n220: \n221: ---\n222: \n223: ## 13. REVIEW MODE\n224: \n225: Review mode has been split into a separate skill. See `deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md`.\n\n(End of file - total 225 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n---\n\n# Deep Research Quick Reference\n\nOne-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nLookup surface during runs covering when to invoke the loop, what each phase produces, how convergence is computed, and where live state lives on disk. Defer to the full protocol and convergence references for deep reasoning.\n\nOperator contract source of truth for this page:\n- command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/start-research-loop.md`\n- convergence stop contract: `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, and the deep-research YAML workflow\n- state packet contract: `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n---\n\n# Deep Research Quick Reference\n\nOne-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nLookup surface during runs covering when to invoke the loop, what each phase produces, how convergence is computed, and where live state lives on disk. Defer to the full protocol and convergence references for deep reasoning.\n\nOperator contract source of truth for this page:\n- command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/start-research-loop.md`\n- convergence stop contract: `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, and the deep-research YAML workflow\n- state packet contract: `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\n\n---\n\n## 2. COMMANDS\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `/deep:start-research-loop:auto \"topic\"` | Run autonomous deep research (no approval gates) |\n| `/deep:start-research-loop:confirm \"topic\"` | Run with approval gates at each iteration |\n| `/deep:start-research-loop \"topic\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `--max-iterations` | 10 | Maximum loop iterations |\n| `--convergence` | 0.05 | Stop when avg newInfoRatio below this |\n| `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n| `progressiveSynthesis` | true | Allow incremental `research/research.md` updates before final synthesis |\n\n---\n\n## 3. WHEN TO USE\n\n| Scenario | Use |\n|----------|-----|\n| Deep unknown topic, multi-round needed | `/deep:start-research-loop` |\n| Simple question, 1-2 sources | Direct search with `@context` |\n| Check prior work only | `memory_context()` |\n| Exhaustive critical research | `/deep:start-research-loop --max-iterations 15 --convergence 0.02` |\n\n---\n\n## 4. ARCHITECTURE\n\n```text\n/deep:start-research-loop  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-research agent (LEAF)\n    |                    |                      |\n    |                    |                      +-- Read state\n    |                    |                      +-- Research (3-5 actions)\n    |                    |                      +-- Write findings\n    |                    |                      +-- Update state\n    |                    |\n    |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n    |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n    |                    +-- Synthesize (final research/research.md)\n    |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. STATE FILES\n\n| File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n|------|----------|--------|---------|\n| Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters |\n| State | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n| Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | What worked/failed, next focus |\n| Registry | `research/findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned open/resolved questions and key findings |\n| Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Reducer-owned lifecycle and convergence summary |\n| Iterations | `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings |\n| Output | `research/research.md` | Markdown | Workflow-owned progressive synthesis output |\n\n> **Live lifecycle branches:** `resume`, `restart`. (`fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not runtime-wired.) `progressiveSynthesis` defaults to `true`, so `research/research.md` is updated during the loop and finalized at synthesis.\n\n> **Path contract:** root-spec runs write directly to `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase first runs use the local `{spec_folder}/research/` directory directly, with `{ownerSlug}-pt-NN` allocated only when prior non-matching content already exists.\n\n> **Canonical pause sentinel:** `research/.deep-research-pause`\n\n> **Runtime capability matrix:** `.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md` and `.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n\n---\n\n## 6. ITERATION STATUS LEGEND\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n|--------|---------|\n| `complete` | Normal iteration with findings |\n| `timeout` | Exceeded time/tool budget |\n| `error` | Failed to produce outputs |\n| `stuck` | No new information found |\n| `insight` | Low ratio but conceptual breakthrough |\n| `thought` | Analytical-only, no evidence |\n\n---\n\n## 7. CONVERGENCE DECISION TREE\n\n```text\nMax iterations reached?\n  Yes --> STOP\n\nAll questions answered?\n  Yes --> STOP\n\nstuckThreshold consecutive no-progress?\n  Yes --> STUCK_RECOVERY\n    Recovery works? --> CONTINUE\n    Recovery fails? --> STOP (with gaps)\n\nComposite convergence (3-signal weighted > 0.60)?\n  Yes --> STOP (converged)\n\nOtherwise --> CONTINUE\n```\n\n### 3-Signal Convergence Model\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Votes STOP When |\n|--------|--------|---------------|-----------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | 3 | avg(last 3 newInfoRatios) < convergenceThreshold |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.35 | 4 | latest ratio <= MAD * 1.4826 |\n| Question Entropy | 0.35 | 1 | answered / total questions >= 0.85 |\n\n**Composite stop threshold:** 0.60 -- weighted stop score must exceed this before quality guards are evaluated.\n\nQuality guards (source diversity, focus alignment, no single-weak-source) must pass before STOP.\n\n---\n\n## 8. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n\nEach @deep-research iteration:\n1. Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` and `deep-research-strategy.md`\n2. Determine focus from reducer-owned strategy \"Next Focus\"\n3. Execute 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n4. Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with findings\n5. Append iteration record to `deep-research-state.jsonl`\n6. Let the workflow reducer update `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n7. Optionally update machine-owned sections in `research/research.md` when progressive synthesis is enabled\n\n---\n\n## 9. TUNING GUIDE\n\n| Goal | Adjustment |\n|------|------------|\n| Deeper research | Lower convergence (0.02), raise max iterations (15) |\n| Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.10), lower max iterations (5) |\n| Broader coverage | Start with broad topic, let iterations narrow |\n| Specific answer | Start with specific question, lower max iterations (5) |\n\n---\n\n## 10. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| Problem | Fix |\n|---------|-----|\n| Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.05 to 0.02 |\n| Repeats same research | Check strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\" is being read |\n| Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n| State file corrupt | Validate JSONL: `cat research/deep-research-state.jsonl \\| jq .` |\n| Loop runs too long | Set lower `--max-iterations` or higher `--convergence` |\n\n---\n\n## 11. PROGRESS VISUALIZATION\n\nAfter each iteration, the orchestrator can display a text-based convergence summary:\n\n### Format\n\n| Element | Format | Example |\n|---------|--------|---------|\n| newInfoRatio trend | ASCII sparkline | `[0.9 0.7 0.5 0.3 0.1]` |\n| Question coverage | Progress bar | `[=======>...] 7/10 (70%)` |\n| Composite score | Threshold bar | `[####----] 0.42 / 0.60` |\n| Noise floor | Comparison | `ratio: 0.12 > floor: 0.08` |\n\n### Example Output\n\n```text\nITERATION 5 PROGRESS\n─────────────────────\nnewInfoRatio: 0.9 -> 0.7 -> 0.5 -> 0.3 -> 0.1  trending down\nQuestions:   [========>..] 8/10 answered (80%)\nComposite:   [######--] 0.48 / 0.60 threshold\nNoise floor: 0.08 (ratio 0.10 ABOVE floor)\nStuck count: 0 | Segment: 1 | Recovery: none\nSignals: RollingAvg=STOP MAD=CONTINUE Entropy=CONTINUE\n```\n\n### When to Display\n\n- After each iteration evaluation (Step 4)\n- In the convergence report (synthesis phase)\n- In confirm mode approval gates\n\n---\n\n## 12. RELATED\n\n| Resource | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `@context` | Single-pass codebase search (not iterative) |\n| `@orchestrate` | Multi-agent coordination |\n| `memory_context()` | Prior work retrieval |\n| `generate-context.js` | Supported memory save script |\n| `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` | Convergence signal details |\n| `references/state/state_jsonl.md` | JSONL state record details |\n\n---\n\n## 13. REVIEW MODE\n\nReview mode has been split into a separate skill. See `deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":225,"totalLines":225,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md","time":{"start":1780735948285,"end":1780735948298}},"id":"prt_e9c223364001iw3XX766ZRUk79","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c220e13001CizcxDAsggJ3Ev"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735948979,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_03_lzUxdsT4HCnh2oQyJEu97823","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Loop Protocol Reference\n3: description: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Loop Protocol Reference\n7: \n8: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n13: \n14: ### Purpose\n15: \n16: Define the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\n17: \n18: ### When to Use\n19: \n20: Load this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.\n21: \n22: ### Core Principle\n23: \n24: The YAML workflow owns lifecycle orchestration, `@deep-research` executes LEAF iterations, and the reducer synchronizes packet state after each iteration and lifecycle transition.\n25: \n26: ### Phase Model\n27: \n28: The deep research loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save.\n29: \n30: Runtime capability matrix references for parity-sensitive loop behavior:\n31: - Human-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n32: - Machine-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n33: \n34: ```text\n35: ┌──────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n36: │  INIT    │────>│  LOOP                    │────>│  SYNTHESIS            │────>│  SAVE    │\n37: │          │     │  ┌────────────────────┐  │     │                       │     │          │\n38: │ Config    │     │  │ Read State         │  │     │ Final                 │     │ Memory   │\n39: │ Strategy │     │  │ Check Convergence  │  │     │ research/research.md  │     │ Context  │\n40: │ State    │     │  │ Dispatch Agent     │  │     │ compilation           │     │ Save     │\n41: │          │     │  │ Evaluate Results   │  │     │                       │     │          │\n42: │          │     │  │ Loop Decision      │  │     │                       │     │          │\n43: │          │     │  └────────┬───────────┘  │     │                       │     │          │\n44: │          │     │           │ repeat       │     │                       │     │          │\n45: └──────────┘     └──────────────────────────┘     └───────────────────────┘     └──────────┘\n46: ```\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## 2. PHASE: INITIALIZATION\n51: \n52: ### Purpose\n53: Set up all state files for a new research session.\n54: \n55: ### Steps\n56: \n57: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n58:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n59:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n60:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n61:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n62: 2. **Resolve canonical artifact names**:\n63:    - Read legacy aliases during the migration window if needed\n64:    - Write only canonical `deep-research-*` names\n65:    - Emit a `migration` event for every legacy alias consumed\n66: 3. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n67: 4. **Write config**: `research/deep-research-config.json` from template + user parameters\n68: 5. **Initialize state log**: First line of `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` with config record\n69: 6. **Initialize strategy**: `research/deep-research-strategy.md` from template with:\n70:    - Topic from user input\n71:    - Initial key questions (3-5, from topic analysis)\n72:    - Known context from `memory_context()` results (if any), injected only after the strategy file exists\n73:    - Research boundaries from config\n74: 6a. **Detect resource-map integration state**:\n75:    - Check `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` once during init\n76:    - If present: set `resource_map_present = true` in `deep-research-config.json`\n77:    - Summarize the map into `deep-research-strategy.md` `Known Context`\n78:    - The summary MUST include per-section entry counts for `READMEs`, `Documents`, `Commands`, `Agents`, `Skills`, `Specs`, `Scripts`, `Tests`, `Config`, and `Meta`\n79:    - The summary MUST also include a one-line theme summary for each resource-map section\n80:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false` and append `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` to `Known Context`\n81: 7. **Initialize findings registry**: `research/findings-registry.json` with empty `openQuestions`, `resolvedQuestions`, `keyFindings`, and `ruledOutDirections`\n82: 7a. **Validate Research Charter**:\n83:    - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Non-Goals\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n84:    - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Stop Conditions\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n85:    - If either section is missing, append it as an empty placeholder before proceeding\n86:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (topic, key questions, non-goals, stop conditions) for user review before proceeding\n87:    - In **auto mode**: accept the charter automatically and continue\n88: 8. **Resume only if config, JSONL, and strategy agree**; otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing\n89: \n90: ### Outputs\n91: - `research/deep-research-config.json`\n92: - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` (1 line)\n93: - `research/deep-research-strategy.md`\n94: \n95: ### Auto-Resume Protocol\n96: If state files already exist from a prior session:\n97: 1. Verify config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\n98: 2. Read JSONL, count iteration records\n99: 3. Read strategy.md for current state\n100: 4. Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n101: 5. Append the canonical resume event to `deep-research-state.jsonl` (all fields below are required by the reducer):\n102: \n103: ```json\n104: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T14:05:00Z\"}\n105: ```\n106: \n107: 6. Continue loop from `step_read_state`.\n108: \n109: ### Lifecycle Branch Contract (current release)\n110: \n111: The runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures; until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n112: \n113: | Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n114: |------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n115: | `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n116: | `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n117: | `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `research/` tree moved under `research_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n118: \n119: **Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n120: \n121: ```json\n122: {\n123:   \"type\": \"event\",\n124:   \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n125:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n126:   \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n127:   \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n128:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n129:   \"generation\": <number>,\n130:   \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n131:   \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n132:   \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n133: }\n134: ```\n135: \n136: Every field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ## 3. PHASE: ITERATION LOOP\n141: \n142: ### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n143: \n144: #### Step 1: Read State\n145: - Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, get last newInfoRatio\n146: - Read `deep-research-strategy.md` -- get next focus, remaining questions\n147: \n148: #### Step 2: Check Convergence\n149: Run the convergence algorithm (see convergence.md):\n150: - Max iterations reached? STOP\n151: - Stuck count >= threshold? STUCK_RECOVERY\n152: - Average newInfoRatio < threshold? STOP\n153: - All questions answered? STOP\n154: - Otherwise: CONTINUE\n155: \n156: #### Step 2c: Quality Guard Check\n157: \n158: When the convergence algorithm returns STOP:\n159: 1. Run quality guard checks (see convergence.md §2.4)\n160: 2. Verify minimum coverage, source diversity, and question resolution thresholds\n161: 3. If **all guards pass**: proceed with STOP, exit to synthesis\n162: 4. If **any guard fails**: override decision to CONTINUE\n163:    - Log each violation: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"guard_violation\",\"guard\":\"<name>\",\"iteration\":N,\"detail\":\"<reason>\"}`\n164:    - Persist the blocked legal-stop outcome: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"blockedBy\":[\"<gate>\"],\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":true,\"score\":0.0},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":false,\"answered\":X,\"total\":Y},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":false,\"sources\":N},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":true}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"<one-line hint>\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n165:    - Append failed guard details to strategy.md \"Active Risks\" section\n166: 5. The loop continues until BOTH convergence AND quality guards pass simultaneously\n167: 6. Guard checks apply only to STOP decisions - CONTINUE and STUCK_RECOVERY bypass this step\n168: \n169: If the legal-stop decision tree returns `blocked`, the workflow MUST append the `blocked_stop` JSONL event before continuing. Reducers and dashboards consume the persisted event; they must not infer blocked-stop state solely from prose logs.\n170: \n171: #### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n172: \n173: Before dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n174: \n175: 1. Check if `research/.deep-research-pause` exists\n176: 2. If present:\n177:    - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n178:    - Halt the loop with message:\n179:      ```text\n180:      Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\n181:      Current state: Iteration {N}, {remaining} questions remaining.\n182:      ```\n183:    - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n184: 3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n185:    - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n186:    - Continue from step_read_state\n187: \n188: Pause and recovery events use the frozen stop-reason enum on the live path. Raw `paused` and `stuck_recovery` labels are legacy aliases and MUST be normalized to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` at emission time.\n189: \n190: **Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause research between iterations.\n191: \n192: #### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n193: \n194: Generate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n195: \n196: ```text\n197: STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n198: Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {N} of {max}\n199: Questions: {answered}/{total} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n200: Last 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n201: Recovery: {active_recovery_strategy or \"none\"}\n202: Next focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n203: ```\n204: \n205: This summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete. It serves as a redundant context channel.\n206: \n207: #### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n208: Dispatch `@deep-research` with explicit context:\n209: ```text\n210: {state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n211: \n212: Research Topic: {config.topic}\n213: Iteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\n214: Focus Area: {strategy.nextFocus}\n215: Remaining Questions: {strategy.remainingQuestions}\n216: Last 3 Iterations Summary: {brief summaries}\n217: Resource Map: if `config.resource_map_present == true`, prior-inventoried files are listed in `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.\n218: State Files:\n219:   - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\n220:   - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\n221:   - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\n222: Output: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n223: CONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\n224: ```\n225: \n226: #### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n227: \n228: Before dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n229: \n230: - `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-research` agent with model Opus.\n231: - `cli-codex` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `codex exec --model X -c model_reasoning_effort=Y -c service_tier=Z -c approval_policy=never --sandbox workspace-write`.\n232: - `cli-gemini` (spec 019): positional prompt to `gemini \"$(cat prompt)\" -m X -s none -y -o text`. Model whitelist enforced (`gemini-3.1-pro-preview` only). No reasoning-effort or service-tier flags.\n233: - `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only); we override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n234: \n235: All branches share:\n236: 1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n237: 2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n238: 3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n239: \n240: Per-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n241: \n242: Cross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope; see the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n243: \n244: Failure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n245: \n246: The dispatch context may include a suggested `focusTrack` label (e.g., `\"focusTrack\": \"performance\"`, `\"focusTrack\": \"security\"`). Agents may tag their iteration with this track label for post-hoc grouping and analysis. Track labels are metadata only - the orchestrator does not use them for loop decisions.\n247: \n248: #### Step 3a: Per-Iteration Budget\n249: \n250: After dispatch, the orchestrator monitors the running iteration against budget limits:\n251: - **Tool call count**: tracked against `config.maxToolCallsPerIteration` (default: 12)\n252: - **Elapsed time**: tracked against `config.maxMinutesPerIteration` (default: 10)\n253: - If either limit is exceeded and no iteration file has been written yet:\n254:   1. Mark the iteration as `\"status\": \"timeout\"` in the JSONL record\n255:   2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"iteration_timeout\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"tool_calls|elapsed_time\"}`\n256:   3. Continue to the next iteration (do not retry the timed-out iteration)\n257: - Budget limits are soft caps - if the agent is actively writing its iteration file when the limit is reached, allow completion\n258: \n259: #### Step 4: Evaluate Results\n260: After agent completes:\n261: 1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n262: 2. Verify JSONL was appended with iteration record\n263: 3. Run reducer with `{ latestJSONLDelta, newIterationFile, priorReducedState }`\n264:    - This is a **delta refresh**, not a full replay of every historical JSONL row on each iteration.\n265:    - The reducer consumes only the newest JSONL slice plus the latest iteration artifact against the previously reduced packet state.\n266: 4. Verify reducer refreshed `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n267: 5. Verify the refreshed packet surfaces reflect the new iteration evidence\n268: 6. Extract `newInfoRatio` from JSONL record\n269: 7. Track stuck count: skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change), reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress), increment if `newInfoRatio < config.convergenceThreshold`, reset otherwise\n270: \n271: #### Step 4a: Generate Dashboard\n272: \n273: After evaluating iteration results, generate a human-readable dashboard:\n274: \n275: 1. Read JSONL state log, findings registry, and strategy.md\n276: 2. Generate or regenerate `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` with the following sections:\n277:    - **Iteration table**: `| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |`\n278:    - **Question status**: `X/Y answered` with itemized list (answered vs remaining)\n279:    - **Trend**: Last 3 newInfoRatio values with direction indicator (ascending, descending, flat)\n280:    - **Dead ends**: Consolidated from all iteration `ruledOut` data\n281:    - **Next focus**: Current value from strategy.md\n282:    - **Active risks**: Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings\n283: 3. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":N}`\n284: 4. The dashboard is **auto-generated only** - never manually edited\n285: 5. The dashboard file is overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n286: 6. Dashboard generation is non-blocking: if it fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n287: \n288: In **confirm mode**, the dashboard is displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate. In **auto mode**, it is written silently for post-hoc review.\n289: \n290: #### Step 4b: Checkpoint Commit (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n291: \n292: This checkpointing pattern is documented for reference, but current runtimes should not assume it is available.\n293: \n294: After each iteration is verified (JSONL appended, iteration file written, reducer outputs refreshed):\n295: \n296: 1. **Stage targeted files only** (never `git add -A`):\n297:    ```bash\n298:    git add research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n299:    git add research/deep-research-state.jsonl\n300:    git add research/deep-research-strategy.md\n301:    git add research/findings-registry.json\n302:    git add research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n303:    git add research/research.md  # if it exists\n304:    ```\n305: 2. **Sanitize**: Exclude `.env`, credentials, large binaries from staging\n306: 3. **Commit**: `git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"`\n307: 4. **On commit failure**: Log warning and continue (checkpoint is non-blocking)\n308: \n309: Checkpoint commits provide rollback points: `git log -- research/` shows the last good state for the research packet. If state corruption occurs, `git checkout HEAD~1 -- research/deep-research-state.jsonl` restores the previous version.\n310: \n311: #### Step 5: Loop Decision\n312: - If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n313: - If STUCK_RECOVERY: modify focus directive, reset stuck count, continue\n314: - Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n315: \n316: ### Ideas Backlog Convention\n317: \n318: A persistent ideas file at `research/research-ideas.md` serves as a parking lot for promising directions not yet pursued.\n319: \n320: #### Check Points\n321: \n322: The orchestrator checks the ideas backlog at three points:\n323: \n324: 1. **Init**: During strategy initialization, if `research/research-ideas.md` exists from a prior session, read it and incorporate relevant ideas into the initial key questions or \"Next Focus\"\n325: 2. **Stuck**: During stuck recovery (Step 2a of the recovery protocol in convergence.md), check ideas backlog before defaulting to generic recovery strategies. Deferred ideas often provide the best escape from stuck states\n326: 3. **Resume**: On auto-resume, read the ideas file alongside JSONL and strategy.md to restore full context\n327: \n328: #### Format\n329: \n330: ```markdown\n331: Title: Research Ideas\n332: \n333: Section: Deferred (not yet explored)\n334: - [Idea description] (noted iteration N: [why deferred])\n335: - [Idea description] (noted iteration N: [why deferred])\n336: \n337: Section: Promoted (moved to Key Questions)\n338: - [Idea] -> promoted to Key Question in iteration N\n339: ```\n340: \n341: Users can edit `research-ideas.md` between sessions to steer future iterations. Agents append new ideas during iterations when they encounter promising tangents that fall outside the current focus.\n342: \n343: ### Stuck Recovery Protocol\n344: When stuckThreshold consecutive iterations show no progress (default: 3, configurable via config.json):\n345: \n346: **Step 0: Classify Failure Mode**\n347: Before selecting a recovery strategy, classify why progress stalled:\n348: 1. Read the last N iteration files (where N = stuckThreshold) to determine the failure pattern\n349: 2. Classify into one of the following modes:\n350:    - `shallow_sources` - iterations find content but lack depth or authoritative sources\n351:    - `contradictory` - iterations return conflicting information without resolution\n352:    - `too_broad` - focus area is too wide, producing scattered low-value findings\n353:    - `repetitive` - iterations keep rediscovering the same information\n354:    - `exhausted` - the topic area has been thoroughly explored with diminishing returns\n355: 3. Select a targeted recovery prompt based on the classification (see convergence.md §4 for category-specific strategies)\n356: 4. Log classification: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_classified\",\"mode\":\"<classification>\",\"iteration\":N}`\n357: \n358: **Steps 1-5: Execute Recovery**\n359: 1. Read strategy.md \"What Worked\" section\n360: 2. Identify least-explored question from \"Key Questions\"\n361: 3. Set next focus to: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope to {least-explored-area}. Try a fundamentally different approach.\" (refined by classification)\n362: 4. Reset stuck counter\n363: 5. If recovery iteration also shows no progress: exit to synthesis with gaps documented\n364: \n365: ### Step 3b: Direct Mode Fallback (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n366: \n367: When agent dispatch fails after the earlier recovery tiers are exhausted:\n368: \n369: 1. Detect dispatch failure: Task tool timeout, API overload (529), or agent crash\n370: 2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"direct_mode\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"dispatch_failure\"}`\n371: 3. Orchestrator absorbs the iteration work:\n372:    - Read state files (JSONL + strategy.md)\n373:    - Determine focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n374:    - Execute 3-5 research actions directly\n375:    - Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n376:    - Update strategy.md\n377:    - Append iteration record to JSONL\n378: 4. Continue loop normally after direct-mode iteration completes\n379: 5. If direct mode also fails, escalate to the final user-escalation tier\n380: \n381: **Note**: Direct mode iterations are logged with `\"directMode\": true` in their JSONL record for diagnostic tracking.\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## 4. WAVE ORCHESTRATION PROTOCOL (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n386: \n387: An optional parallel execution concept for research topics with multiple independent questions. Treat this as reference guidance only; the live workflow remains sequential and does **not** emit wave-specific JSONL events or routing today.\n388: \n389: ### When to Use Waves\n390: \n391: - 3+ independent key questions identified during initialization\n392: - Questions do not depend on each other's answers\n393: - Parallelism is beneficial (time-constrained research, broad survey)\n394: \n395: ### Wave Execution Model (conceptual only)\n396: \n397: ```text\n398: Wave 1: Dispatch N agents on independent questions\n399:   |\n400:   +-- Agent A: Question 1 --> iteration-001.md (newInfoRatio: 0.8)\n401:   +-- Agent B: Question 2 --> iteration-002.md (newInfoRatio: 0.3)\n402:   +-- Agent C: Question 3 --> iteration-003.md (newInfoRatio: 0.7)\n403:   |\n404: Scoring: Rank by newInfoRatio, prune below median only in a future runtime that explicitly adds wave support\n405:   |\n406: Wave 2: Follow-up on top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2))\n407:   +-- Agent A: Question 1 follow-up --> iteration-004.md\n408:   +-- Agent C: Question 3 follow-up --> iteration-005.md\n409:   |\n410: Repeat until convergence\n411: ```\n412: \n413: ### Scoring and Pruning\n414: \n415: In a future wave-enabled runtime:\n416: 1. Rank all wave iterations by `newInfoRatio`\n417: 2. Compute wave median: `median([i.newInfoRatio for i in wave_iterations])`\n418: 3. **Prune**: Questions with newInfoRatio below median would be deprioritized\n419: 4. **Promote**: Top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2)) would get follow-up iterations\n420: 5. Pruned questions would move to the ideas backlog, not be discarded\n421: \n422: ### Breakthrough Detection\n423: \n424: When any single iteration in a wave achieves `newInfoRatio > 2x wave_average`:\n425: \n426: 1. Flag as **breakthrough**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"breakthrough\",\"iteration\":N,\"ratio\":X.XX}`\n427: 2. Generate 2-3 adjacent questions from the breakthrough findings\n428: 3. Prioritize these adjacent questions in the next wave\n429: 4. Breakthrough iterations are NEVER pruned\n430: \n431: ### Wave JSONL Records\n432: \n433: Wave-specific fields and events are **not part of the current persisted contract**. Until a runtime explicitly ships wave support, keep iteration records and events on the standard sequential schema only.\n434: \n435: ### Integration with Sequential Loop\n436: \n437: - Waves are an ALTERNATIVE to sequential iteration, not a replacement\n438: - The convergence algorithm applies identically (uses all iteration records)\n439: - A future wave-capable runtime could transition back to sequential mode when questions narrow to 1-2\n440: - The current runtime never spawns a wave automatically\n441: \n442: ---\n443: \n444: ## 5. CONTEXT ISOLATION DISPATCH (EXPERIMENTAL, REFERENCE-ONLY)\n445: \n446: An alternative dispatch mechanism that guarantees fresh context per iteration by launching a new OS process. Treat this as reference-only unless the runtime explicitly implements alternate CLI dispatch.\n447: \n448: ### Motivation\n449: \n450: The standard dispatch (Task tool) shares the parent session's token budget. In long research sessions (10+ iterations), this may cause context compression that degrades reasoning quality. Process-level isolation eliminates this risk.\n451: \n452: ### Dispatch Mechanism\n453: \n454: Replace Task tool dispatch with shell-level `claude -p` invocation:\n455: \n456: 1. **Generate prompt**: Orchestrator builds a self-contained prompt from:\n457:    - Strategy.md (current state)\n458:    - Config.json (parameters)\n459:    - Last N iteration summaries (from JSONL)\n460:    - Compact state summary (Step 2b)\n461:    - Full agent protocol instructions\n462: 2. **Write to temp file**: `scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md`\n463: 3. **Execute**: `claude -p \"$(cat scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md)\" --max-turns 50 --output-format json`\n464: 4. **Collect output**: Agent writes iteration file directly to disk\n465: 5. **Verify**: Orchestrator checks iteration file and JSONL were created\n466: 6. **Cleanup**: Remove temp prompt file\n467: \n468: ### Trade-offs\n469: \n470: | Aspect | Task Tool Dispatch | `claude -p` Dispatch |\n471: |--------|-------------------|---------------------|\n472: | Context freshness | Shared budget, may degrade | Guaranteed fresh |\n473: | Token cost | Lower (cached context) | Higher (full context per call) |\n474: | Latency | Lower (in-process) | Higher (new process startup) |\n475: | Context size | Limited by parent budget | Full model context available |\n476: | Error handling | In-process exceptions | Process exit codes |\n477: \n478: ### When to Use\n479: \n480: - Autonomous/unattended research sessions (overnight runs)\n481: - Research past iteration 8+ where context degradation is measurable\n482: - Critical research where reasoning quality must not degrade\n483: \n484: **Status**: Reference-only. Track adoption based on need for fully autonomous overnight research sessions.\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: ## 6. PHASE: SYNTHESIS\n489: \n490: ### Purpose\n491: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md. The synthesis workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md` output.\n492: \n493: ### Steps\n494: \n495: 1. **Read all iteration files**: `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n496: 2. **Read strategy.md**: Final state of questions, approaches\n497: 3. **Compile research/research.md**: Merge findings into 17-section format\n498:    - Deduplicate overlapping findings\n499:    - Organize by section topic\n500:    - Add citations from iteration files\n501:    - Cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in the References section when `config.resource_map_present == true`\n502:    - Do not synthesize a placeholder reference when `resource-map.md` was absent at init\n503:    - Note unanswered questions in Section 12 (Open Questions)\n504:    - **Include a mandatory \"## Eliminated Alternatives\" section** as primary research output:\n505:      - Consolidate all `ruledOut` entries from iteration JSONL records\n506:      - Consolidate all `## Dead Ends` sections from iteration files\n507:      - Format as a table: `| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |`\n508:      - This section documents negative knowledge (what was tried and why it failed)\n509:      - Treat as primary research output - not an appendix or afterthought\n510:      - Place after Section 11 (Recommendations) and before Section 12 (Open Questions)\n511: 4. **If reopening a completed packet later**: snapshot this file as `research/synthesis-v{generation}.md` before any `completed-continue` flow\n512: 5. **Update config status**: Set `status: \"complete\"` in config.json\n513: 6. **Final JSONL entry**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":N,\"answeredCount\":A,\"totalQuestions\":Q,\"stopReason\":\"converged\"}`\n514: \n515: ### Progressive vs Final Synthesis\n516: - If `progressiveSynthesis: true` (default): research/research.md was updated each iteration. Final synthesis is a cleanup pass.\n517: - If `progressiveSynthesis: false`: research/research.md is created from scratch during synthesis.\n518: \n519: ---\n520: \n521: ## 7. PHASE: SAVE\n522: \n523: ### Purpose\n524: Preserve research context to memory system.\n525: \n526: ### Steps\n527: \n528: 1. **Generate context**: `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js {spec_folder}`\n529: 2. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow\n530: 3. **Verify**: Confirm memory/*.md file created with proper anchors\n531: \n532: ---\n533: \n534: ## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS\n535: \n536: ```text\n537: [INITIALIZED] --> config + strategy + state created\n538:     |\n539: [ITERATING] --> agent dispatched, executing research\n540:     |\n541: [EVALUATING] --> iteration complete, checking convergence\n542:     |\n543:     |-- newInfoRatio >= threshold --> [ITERATING]\n544:     |-- stuck_count >= stuckThreshold --> [STUCK_RECOVERY]\n545:     |-- converged or max_iterations --> [SYNTHESIZING]\n546: \n547: [STUCK_RECOVERY] --> widen focus, try different approach\n548:     |\n549:     |-- recovered (newInfoRatio > 0) --> [ITERATING]\n550:     |-- still stuck --> [SYNTHESIZING] (gaps documented)\n551: \n552: [SYNTHESIZING] --> final research/research.md compilation\n553:     |\n554: [SAVING] --> memory context preservation\n555:     |\n556: [COMPLETE] --> all artifacts created, loop finished\n557: ```\n558: \n559: Hook-capable and non-hook runtimes must follow the same state machine. Hooks may pre-prime context, but they must not change which lifecycle branch the packet selects.\n560: \n561: ---\n562: \n563: ## 9. ERROR HANDLING\n564: \n565: | Error | Phase | Action |\n566: |-------|-------|--------|\n567: | Agent dispatch timeout | Loop | Retry once with reduced scope. If second timeout, mark iteration as \"timeout\" and continue |\n568: | WebFetch fails | Loop | Log URL in iteration file, try alternative source, continue with available data |\n569: | State file missing | Init/Loop | If JSONL missing: re-initialize. If strategy missing: reconstruct from JSONL |\n570: | JSONL malformed | Loop | Skip malformed lines, reconstruct from valid entries |\n571: | 3+ consecutive failures | Loop | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n572: | Agent dispatch failure (API overload, timeout) | Loop | Escalate through the documented recovery ladder in order. Direct mode fallback is reference-only unless the runtime explicitly supports it. |\n573: | Memory save fails | Save | Preserve the current `{artifact_dir}` packet as backup, then log the error |\n574: \n575: ### State Recovery Protocol\n576: \n577: When state files are missing or corrupted, apply this 5-priority cascade:\n578: \n579: | Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n580: |----------|-----------|----------------|\n581: | 1 (Primary) | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation (with fault-tolerant parsing) |\n582: | 2 (Strategy rebuild) | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract questions, focus areas, newInfoRatio trend. Create minimal strategy.md |\n583: | 3 (JSONL reconstruction) | JSONL missing/corrupt, iteration files exist | Scan `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`, parse Assessment sections, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n584: | 4 (Config-only restart) | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase using config parameters. Log: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fresh_restart\",\"reason\":\"state_files_missing\"}` |\n585: | 5 (Abort) | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n586: \n587: Each priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next. See state_format.md for JSONL reconstruction details.\n588: \n589: ---\n590: \n591: ## 10. CONFIRM MODE ADDITIONS\n592: \n593: In confirm mode, the YAML workflow adds approval gates:\n594: \n595: | Gate Location | Behavior |\n596: |---------------|----------|\n597: | After initialization | Show config and initial strategy. Wait for approval |\n598: | After each iteration | Show iteration findings and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n599: | Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n600: | After synthesis | Show final research/research.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n601: \n602: ---\n603: \n604: ## 11. REVIEW MODE ROUTING\n605: \n606: Deep-review lifecycle, convergence, state schemas, traceability protocols, and report contracts live in the sibling `deep-review` skill.\n607: \n608: This reference keeps only the routing rule: do not document or execute review-mode loop behavior from `deep-research`. Route review requests to `deep-review/SKILL.md` and its references.\n\n(End of file - total 608 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Loop Protocol Reference\ndescription: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\n---\n\n# Loop Protocol Reference\n\nCanonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","text":"---\ntitle: Loop Protocol Reference\ndescription: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\n---\n\n# Loop Protocol Reference\n\nCanonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nThe YAML workflow owns lifecycle orchestration, `@deep-research` executes LEAF iterations, and the reducer synchronizes packet state after each iteration and lifecycle transition.\n\n### Phase Model\n\nThe deep research loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save.\n\nRuntime capability matrix references for parity-sensitive loop behavior:\n- Human-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n- Machine-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n\n```text\n┌──────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n│  INIT    │────>│  LOOP                    │────>│  SYNTHESIS            │────>│  SAVE    │\n│          │     │  ┌────────────────────┐  │     │                       │     │          │\n│ Config    │     │  │ Read State         │  │     │ Final                 │     │ Memory   │\n│ Strategy │     │  │ Check Convergence  │  │     │ research/research.md  │     │ Context  │\n│ State    │     │  │ Dispatch Agent     │  │     │ compilation           │     │ Save     │\n│          │     │  │ Evaluate Results   │  │     │                       │     │          │\n│          │     │  │ Loop Decision      │  │     │                       │     │          │\n│          │     │  └────────┬───────────┘  │     │                       │     │          │\n│          │     │           │ repeat       │     │                       │     │          │\n└──────────┘     └──────────────────────────┘     └───────────────────────┘     └──────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. PHASE: INITIALIZATION\n\n### Purpose\nSet up all state files for a new research session.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n   - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n   - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n   - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n   - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n2. **Resolve canonical artifact names**:\n   - Read legacy aliases during the migration window if needed\n   - Write only canonical `deep-research-*` names\n   - Emit a `migration` event for every legacy alias consumed\n3. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n4. **Write config**: `research/deep-research-config.json` from template + user parameters\n5. **Initialize state log**: First line of `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` with config record\n6. **Initialize strategy**: `research/deep-research-strategy.md` from template with:\n   - Topic from user input\n   - Initial key questions (3-5, from topic analysis)\n   - Known context from `memory_context()` results (if any), injected only after the strategy file exists\n   - Research boundaries from config\n6a. **Detect resource-map integration state**:\n   - Check `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` once during init\n   - If present: set `resource_map_present = true` in `deep-research-config.json`\n   - Summarize the map into `deep-research-strategy.md` `Known Context`\n   - The summary MUST include per-section entry counts for `READMEs`, `Documents`, `Commands`, `Agents`, `Skills`, `Specs`, `Scripts`, `Tests`, `Config`, and `Meta`\n   - The summary MUST also include a one-line theme summary for each resource-map section\n   - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false` and append `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` to `Known Context`\n7. **Initialize findings registry**: `research/findings-registry.json` with empty `openQuestions`, `resolvedQuestions`, `keyFindings`, and `ruledOutDirections`\n7a. **Validate Research Charter**:\n   - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Non-Goals\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n   - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Stop Conditions\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n   - If either section is missing, append it as an empty placeholder before proceeding\n   - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (topic, key questions, non-goals, stop conditions) for user review before proceeding\n   - In **auto mode**: accept the charter automatically and continue\n8. **Resume only if config, JSONL, and strategy agree**; otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing\n\n### Outputs\n- `research/deep-research-config.json`\n- `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` (1 line)\n- `research/deep-research-strategy.md`\n\n### Auto-Resume Protocol\nIf state files already exist from a prior session:\n1. Verify config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\n2. Read JSONL, count iteration records\n3. Read strategy.md for current state\n4. Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n5. Append the canonical resume event to `deep-research-state.jsonl` (all fields below are required by the reducer):\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T14:05:00Z\"}\n```\n\n6. Continue loop from `step_read_state`.\n\n### Lifecycle Branch Contract (current release)\n\nThe runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures; until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n\n| Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n|------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n| `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n| `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n| `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `research/` tree moved under `research_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n\n**Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n  \"generation\": <number>,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n  \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n}\n```\n\nEvery field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n\n---\n\n## 3. PHASE: ITERATION LOOP\n\n### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n\n#### Step 1: Read State\n- Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, get last newInfoRatio\n- Read `deep-research-strategy.md` -- get next focus, remaining questions\n\n#### Step 2: Check Convergence\nRun the convergence algorithm (see convergence.md):\n- Max iterations reached? STOP\n- Stuck count >= threshold? STUCK_RECOVERY\n- Average newInfoRatio < threshold? STOP\n- All questions answered? STOP\n- Otherwise: CONTINUE\n\n#### Step 2c: Quality Guard Check\n\nWhen the convergence algorithm returns STOP:\n1. Run quality guard checks (see convergence.md §2.4)\n2. Verify minimum coverage, source diversity, and question resolution thresholds\n3. If **all guards pass**: proceed with STOP, exit to synthesis\n4. If **any guard fails**: override decision to CONTINUE\n   - Log each violation: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"guard_violation\",\"guard\":\"<name>\",\"iteration\":N,\"detail\":\"<reason>\"}`\n   - Persist the blocked legal-stop outcome: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"blockedBy\":[\"<gate>\"],\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":true,\"score\":0.0},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":false,\"answered\":X,\"total\":Y},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":false,\"sources\":N},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":true}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"<one-line hint>\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n   - Append failed guard details to strategy.md \"Active Risks\" section\n5. The loop continues until BOTH convergence AND quality guards pass simultaneously\n6. Guard checks apply only to STOP decisions - CONTINUE and STUCK_RECOVERY bypass this step\n\nIf the legal-stop decision tree returns `blocked`, the workflow MUST append the `blocked_stop` JSONL event before continuing. Reducers and dashboards consume the persisted event; they must not infer blocked-stop state solely from prose logs.\n\n#### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n\nBefore dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n\n1. Check if `research/.deep-research-pause` exists\n2. If present:\n   - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n   - Halt the loop with message:\n     ```text\n     Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\n     Current state: Iteration {N}, {remaining} questions remaining.\n     ```\n   - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n   - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n   - Continue from step_read_state\n\nPause and recovery events use the frozen stop-reason enum on the live path. Raw `paused` and `stuck_recovery` labels are legacy aliases and MUST be normalized to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` at emission time.\n\n**Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause research between iterations.\n\n#### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n\nGenerate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n\n```text\nSTATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\nSegment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {N} of {max}\nQuestions: {answered}/{total} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\nLast 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\nRecovery: {active_recovery_strategy or \"none\"}\nNext focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n```\n\nThis summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete. It serves as a redundant context channel.\n\n#### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\nDispatch `@deep-research` with explicit context:\n```text\n{state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n\nResearch Topic: {config.topic}\nIteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\nFocus Area: {strategy.nextFocus}\nRemaining Questions: {strategy.remainingQuestions}\nLast 3 Iterations Summary: {brief summaries}\nResource Map: if `config.resource_map_present == true`, prior-inventoried files are listed in `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.\nState Files:\n  - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\n  - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\n  - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\nOutput: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\nCONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\n```\n\n#### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n\nBefore dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n\n- `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-research` agent with model Opus.\n- `cli-codex` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `codex exec --model X -c model_reasoning_effort=Y -c service_tier=Z -c approval_policy=never --sandbox workspace-write`.\n- `cli-gemini` (spec 019): positional prompt to `gemini \"$(cat prompt)\" -m X -s none -y -o text`. Model whitelist enforced (`gemini-3.1-pro-preview` only). No reasoning-effort or service-tier flags.\n- `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only); we override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n\nAll branches share:\n1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n\nPer-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n\nCross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope; see the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n\nFailure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n\nThe dispatch context may include a suggested `focusTrack` label (e.g., `\"focusTrack\": \"performance\"`, `\"focusTrack\": \"security\"`). Agents may tag their iteration with this track label for post-hoc grouping and analysis. Track labels are metadata only - the orchestrator does not use them for loop decisions.\n\n#### Step 3a: Per-Iteration Budget\n\nAfter dispatch, the orchestrator monitors the running iteration against budget limits:\n- **Tool call count**: tracked against `config.maxToolCallsPerIteration` (default: 12)\n- **Elapsed time**: tracked against `config.maxMinutesPerIteration` (default: 10)\n- If either limit is exceeded and no iteration file has been written yet:\n  1. Mark the iteration as `\"status\": \"timeout\"` in the JSONL record\n  2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"iteration_timeout\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"tool_calls|elapsed_time\"}`\n  3. Continue to the next iteration (do not retry the timed-out iteration)\n- Budget limits are soft caps - if the agent is actively writing its iteration file when the limit is reached, allow completion\n\n#### Step 4: Evaluate Results\nAfter agent completes:\n1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n2. Verify JSONL was appended with iteration record\n3. Run reducer with `{ latestJSONLDelta, newIterationFile, priorReducedState }`\n   - This is a **delta refresh**, not a full replay of every historical JSONL row on each iteration.\n   - The reducer consumes only the newest JSONL slice plus the latest iteration artifact against the previously reduced packet state.\n4. Verify reducer refreshed `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n5. Verify the refreshed packet surfaces reflect the new iteration evidence\n6. Extract `newInfoRatio` from JSONL record\n7. Track stuck count: skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change), reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress), increment if `newInfoRatio < config.convergenceThreshold`, reset otherwise\n\n#### Step 4a: Generate Dashboard\n\nAfter evaluating iteration results, generate a human-readable dashboard:\n\n1. Read JSONL state log, findings registry, and strategy.md\n2. Generate or regenerate `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` with the following sections:\n   - **Iteration table**: `| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |`\n   - **Question status**: `X/Y answered` with itemized list (answered vs remaining)\n   - **Trend**: Last 3 newInfoRatio values with direction indicator (ascending, descending, flat)\n   - **Dead ends**: Consolidated from all iteration `ruledOut` data\n   - **Next focus**: Current value from strategy.md\n   - **Active risks**: Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings\n3. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":N}`\n4. The dashboard is **auto-generated only** - never manually edited\n5. The dashboard file is overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n6. Dashboard generation is non-blocking: if it fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n\nIn **confirm mode**, the dashboard is displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate. In **auto mode**, it is written silently for post-hoc review.\n\n#### Step 4b: Checkpoint Commit (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nThis checkpointing pattern is documented for reference, but current runtimes should not assume it is available.\n\nAfter each iteration is verified (JSONL appended, iteration file written, reducer outputs refreshed):\n\n1. **Stage targeted files only** (never `git add -A`):\n   ```bash\n   git add research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n   git add research/deep-research-state.jsonl\n   git add research/deep-research-strategy.md\n   git add research/findings-registry.json\n   git add research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n   git add research/research.md  # if it exists\n   ```\n2. **Sanitize**: Exclude `.env`, credentials, large binaries from staging\n3. **Commit**: `git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"`\n4. **On commit failure**: Log warning and continue (checkpoint is non-blocking)\n\nCheckpoint commits provide rollback points: `git log -- research/` shows the last good state for the research packet. If state corruption occurs, `git checkout HEAD~1 -- research/deep-research-state.jsonl` restores the previous version.\n\n#### Step 5: Loop Decision\n- If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n- If STUCK_RECOVERY: modify focus directive, reset stuck count, continue\n- Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n\n### Ideas Backlog Convention\n\nA persistent ideas file at `research/research-ideas.md` serves as a parking lot for promising directions not yet pursued.\n\n#### Check Points\n\nThe orchestrator checks the ideas backlog at three points:\n\n1. **Init**: During strategy initialization, if `research/research-ideas.md` exists from a prior session, read it and incorporate relevant ideas into the initial key questions or \"Next Focus\"\n2. **Stuck**: During stuck recovery (Step 2a of the recovery protocol in convergence.md), check ideas backlog before defaulting to generic recovery strategies. Deferred ideas often provide the best escape from stuck states\n3. **Resume**: On auto-resume, read the ideas file alongside JSONL and strategy.md to restore full context\n\n#### Format\n\n```markdown\nTitle: Research Ideas\n\nSection: Deferred (not yet explored)\n- [Idea description] (noted iteration N: [why deferred])\n- [Idea description] (noted iteration N: [why deferred])\n\nSection: Promoted (moved to Key Questions)\n- [Idea] -> promoted to Key Question in iteration N\n```\n\nUsers can edit `research-ideas.md` between sessions to steer future iterations. Agents append new ideas during iterations when they encounter promising tangents that fall outside the current focus.\n\n### Stuck Recovery Protocol\nWhen stuckThreshold consecutive iterations show no progress (default: 3, configurable via config.json):\n\n**Step 0: Classify Failure Mode**\nBefore selecting a recovery strategy, classify why progress stalled:\n1. Read the last N iteration files (where N = stuckThreshold) to determine the failure pattern\n2. Classify into one of the following modes:\n   - `shallow_sources` - iterations find content but lack depth or authoritative sources\n   - `contradictory` - iterations return conflicting information without resolution\n   - `too_broad` - focus area is too wide, producing scattered low-value findings\n   - `repetitive` - iterations keep rediscovering the same information\n   - `exhausted` - the topic area has been thoroughly explored with diminishing returns\n3. Select a targeted recovery prompt based on the classification (see convergence.md §4 for category-specific strategies)\n4. Log classification: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_classified\",\"mode\":\"<classification>\",\"iteration\":N}`\n\n**Steps 1-5: Execute Recovery**\n1. Read strategy.md \"What Worked\" section\n2. Identify least-explored question from \"Key Questions\"\n3. Set next focus to: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope to {least-explored-area}. Try a fundamentally different approach.\" (refined by classification)\n4. Reset stuck counter\n5. If recovery iteration also shows no progress: exit to synthesis with gaps documented\n\n### Step 3b: Direct Mode Fallback (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nWhen agent dispatch fails after the earlier recovery tiers are exhausted:\n\n1. Detect dispatch failure: Task tool timeout, API overload (529), or agent crash\n2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"direct_mode\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"dispatch_failure\"}`\n3. Orchestrator absorbs the iteration work:\n   - Read state files (JSONL + strategy.md)\n   - Determine focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n   - Execute 3-5 research actions directly\n   - Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n   - Update strategy.md\n   - Append iteration record to JSONL\n4. Continue loop normally after direct-mode iteration completes\n5. If direct mode also fails, escalate to the final user-escalation tier\n\n**Note**: Direct mode iterations are logged with `\"directMode\": true` in their JSONL record for diagnostic tracking.\n\n---\n\n## 4. WAVE ORCHESTRATION PROTOCOL (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nAn optional parallel execution concept for research topics with multiple independent questions. Treat this as reference guidance only; the live workflow remains sequential and does **not** emit wave-specific JSONL events or routing today.\n\n### When to Use Waves\n\n- 3+ independent key questions identified during initialization\n- Questions do not depend on each other's answers\n- Parallelism is beneficial (time-constrained research, broad survey)\n\n### Wave Execution Model (conceptual only)\n\n```text\nWave 1: Dispatch N agents on independent questions\n  |\n  +-- Agent A: Question 1 --> iteration-001.md (newInfoRatio: 0.8)\n  +-- Agent B: Question 2 --> iteration-002.md (newInfoRatio: 0.3)\n  +-- Agent C: Question 3 --> iteration-003.md (newInfoRatio: 0.7)\n  |\nScoring: Rank by newInfoRatio, prune below median only in a future runtime that explicitly adds wave support\n  |\nWave 2: Follow-up on top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2))\n  +-- Agent A: Question 1 follow-up --> iteration-004.md\n  +-- Agent C: Question 3 follow-up --> iteration-005.md\n  |\nRepeat until convergence\n```\n\n### Scoring and Pruning\n\nIn a future wave-enabled runtime:\n1. Rank all wave iterations by `newInfoRatio`\n2. Compute wave median: `median([i.newInfoRatio for i in wave_iterations])`\n3. **Prune**: Questions with newInfoRatio below median would be deprioritized\n4. **Promote**: Top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2)) would get follow-up iterations\n5. Pruned questions would move to the ideas backlog, not be discarded\n\n### Breakthrough Detection\n\nWhen any single iteration in a wave achieves `newInfoRatio > 2x wave_average`:\n\n1. Flag as **breakthrough**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"breakthrough\",\"iteration\":N,\"ratio\":X.XX}`\n2. Generate 2-3 adjacent questions from the breakthrough findings\n3. Prioritize these adjacent questions in the next wave\n4. Breakthrough iterations are NEVER pruned\n\n### Wave JSONL Records\n\nWave-specific fields and events are **not part of the current persisted contract**. Until a runtime explicitly ships wave support, keep iteration records and events on the standard sequential schema only.\n\n### Integration with Sequential Loop\n\n- Waves are an ALTERNATIVE to sequential iteration, not a replacement\n- The convergence algorithm applies identically (uses all iteration records)\n- A future wave-capable runtime could transition back to sequential mode when questions narrow to 1-2\n- The current runtime never spawns a wave automatically\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONTEXT ISOLATION DISPATCH (EXPERIMENTAL, REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nAn alternative dispatch mechanism that guarantees fresh context per iteration by launching a new OS process. Treat this as reference-only unless the runtime explicitly implements alternate CLI dispatch.\n\n### Motivation\n\nThe standard dispatch (Task tool) shares the parent session's token budget. In long research sessions (10+ iterations), this may cause context compression that degrades reasoning quality. Process-level isolation eliminates this risk.\n\n### Dispatch Mechanism\n\nReplace Task tool dispatch with shell-level `claude -p` invocation:\n\n1. **Generate prompt**: Orchestrator builds a self-contained prompt from:\n   - Strategy.md (current state)\n   - Config.json (parameters)\n   - Last N iteration summaries (from JSONL)\n   - Compact state summary (Step 2b)\n   - Full agent protocol instructions\n2. **Write to temp file**: `scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md`\n3. **Execute**: `claude -p \"$(cat scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md)\" --max-turns 50 --output-format json`\n4. **Collect output**: Agent writes iteration file directly to disk\n5. **Verify**: Orchestrator checks iteration file and JSONL were created\n6. **Cleanup**: Remove temp prompt file\n\n### Trade-offs\n\n| Aspect | Task Tool Dispatch | `claude -p` Dispatch |\n|--------|-------------------|---------------------|\n| Context freshness | Shared budget, may degrade | Guaranteed fresh |\n| Token cost | Lower (cached context) | Higher (full context per call) |\n| Latency | Lower (in-process) | Higher (new process startup) |\n| Context size | Limited by parent budget | Full model context available |\n| Error handling | In-process exceptions | Process exit codes |\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Autonomous/unattended research sessions (overnight runs)\n- Research past iteration 8+ where context degradation is measurable\n- Critical research where reasoning quality must not degrade\n\n**Status**: Reference-only. Track adoption based on need for fully autonomous overnight research sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. PHASE: SYNTHESIS\n\n### Purpose\nCompile all iteration findings into final research/research.md. The synthesis workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md` output.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Read all iteration files**: `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n2. **Read strategy.md**: Final state of questions, approaches\n3. **Compile research/research.md**: Merge findings into 17-section format\n   - Deduplicate overlapping findings\n   - Organize by section topic\n   - Add citations from iteration files\n   - Cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in the References section when `config.resource_map_present == true`\n   - Do not synthesize a placeholder reference when `resource-map.md` was absent at init\n   - Note unanswered questions in Section 12 (Open Questions)\n   - **Include a mandatory \"## Eliminated Alternatives\" section** as primary research output:\n     - Consolidate all `ruledOut` entries from iteration JSONL records\n     - Consolidate all `## Dead Ends` sections from iteration files\n     - Format as a table: `| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |`\n     - This section documents negative knowledge (what was tried and why it failed)\n     - Treat as primary research output - not an appendix or afterthought\n     - Place after Section 11 (Recommendations) and before Section 12 (Open Questions)\n4. **If reopening a completed packet later**: snapshot this file as `research/synthesis-v{generation}.md` before any `completed-continue` flow\n5. **Update config status**: Set `status: \"complete\"` in config.json\n6. **Final JSONL entry**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":N,\"answeredCount\":A,\"totalQuestions\":Q,\"stopReason\":\"converged\"}`\n\n### Progressive vs Final Synthesis\n- If `progressiveSynthesis: true` (default): research/research.md was updated each iteration. Final synthesis is a cleanup pass.\n- If `progressiveSynthesis: false`: research/research.md is created from scratch during synthesis.\n\n---\n\n## 7. PHASE: SAVE\n\n### Purpose\nPreserve research context to memory system.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Generate context**: `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js {spec_folder}`\n2. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow\n3. **Verify**: Confirm memory/*.md file created with proper anchors\n\n---\n\n## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS\n\n```text\n[INITIALIZED] --> config + strategy + state created\n    |\n[ITERATING] --> agent dispatched, executing research\n    |\n[EVALUATING] --> iteration complete, checking convergence\n    |\n    |-- newInfoRatio >= threshold --> [ITERATING]\n    |-- stuck_count >= stuckThreshold --> [STUCK_RECOVERY]\n    |-- converged or max_iterations --> [SYNTHESIZING]\n\n[STUCK_RECOVERY] --> widen focus, try different approach\n    |\n    |-- recovered (newInfoRatio > 0) --> [ITERATING]\n    |-- still stuck --> [SYNTHESIZING] (gaps documented)\n\n[SYNTHESIZING] --> final research/research.md compilation\n    |\n[SAVING] --> memory context preservation\n    |\n[COMPLETE] --> all artifacts created, loop finished\n```\n\nHook-capable and non-hook runtimes must follow the same state machine. Hooks may pre-prime context, but they must not change which lifecycle branch the packet selects.\n\n---\n\n## 9. ERROR HANDLING\n\n| Error | Phase | Action |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| Agent dispatch timeout | Loop | Retry once with reduced scope. If second timeout, mark iteration as \"timeout\" and continue |\n| WebFetch fails | Loop | Log URL in iteration file, try alternative source, continue with available data |\n| State file missing | Init/Loop | If JSONL missing: re-initialize. If strategy missing: reconstruct from JSONL |\n| JSONL malformed | Loop | Skip malformed lines, reconstruct from valid entries |\n| 3+ consecutive failures | Loop | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n| Agent dispatch failure (API overload, timeout) | Loop | Escalate through the documented recovery ladder in order. Direct mode fallback is reference-only unless the runtime explicitly supports it. |\n| Memory save fails | Save | Preserve the current `{artifact_dir}` packet as backup, then log the error |\n\n### State Recovery Protocol\n\nWhen state files are missing or corrupted, apply this 5-priority cascade:\n\n| Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n|----------|-----------|----------------|\n| 1 (Primary) | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation (with fault-tolerant parsing) |\n| 2 (Strategy rebuild) | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract questions, focus areas, newInfoRatio trend. Create minimal strategy.md |\n| 3 (JSONL reconstruction) | JSONL missing/corrupt, iteration files exist | Scan `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`, parse Assessment sections, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n| 4 (Config-only restart) | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase using config parameters. Log: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fresh_restart\",\"reason\":\"state_files_missing\"}` |\n| 5 (Abort) | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n\nEach priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next. See state_format.md for JSONL reconstruction details.\n\n---\n\n## 10. CONFIRM MODE ADDITIONS\n\nIn confirm mode, the YAML workflow adds approval gates:\n\n| Gate Location | Behavior |\n|---------------|----------|\n| After initialization | Show config and initial strategy. Wait for approval |\n| After each iteration | Show iteration findings and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n| Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n| After synthesis | Show final research/research.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n\n---\n\n## 11. REVIEW MODE ROUTING\n\nDeep-review lifecycle, convergence, state schemas, traceability protocols, and report contracts live in the sibling `deep-review` skill.\n\nThis reference keeps only the routing rule: do not document or execute review-mode loop behavior from `deep-research`. Route review requests to `deep-review/SKILL.md` and its references.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":608,"totalLines":608,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","time":{"start":1780735948971,"end":1780735948976}},"id":"prt_e9c223669001GOG7Ad7W2Ufeuc","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c220e13001CizcxDAsggJ3Ev"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735949693,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_04_iTQn4irx8w10rM2DW9Ti6971","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: State Format Reference\n3: description: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # State Format Reference\n7: \n8: Live state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n13: \n14: ### Purpose\n15: \n16: Summarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\n17: \n18: ### When to Use\n19: \n20: Load this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\n21: \n22: ### Routed Details\n23: \n24: - `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\n25: - `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\n26: - `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\n27: \n28: For iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this skill's live state contract.\n29: \n30: ### Packet Summary\n31: \n32: The deep-research loop persists continuity in packet files so each iteration can run with fresh context.\n33: \n34: | File | Format | Purpose | Mutability |\n35: |------|--------|---------|------------|\n36: | `deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters and lineage | Created at init; read-only after |\n37: | `deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Append-only structured log | Append-only |\n38: | `deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | Current research plan and next focus | Reducer-managed sections |\n39: | `deep-research-findings-registry.json` / `findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned findings and question state | Auto-generated |\n40: | `deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Operator summary | Auto-generated |\n41: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration narrative | Write-once |\n42: | `deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` | JSONL | Per-iteration structured delta | Write-once |\n43: | `research.md` | Markdown | Final/progressive synthesis | Workflow-owned |\n44: | `resource-map.md` | Markdown | Optional evidence-derived resource map | Workflow-owned |\n45: \n46: The artifact directory is resolved by `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`.\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## 2. PACKET LOCATION\n51: \n52: Root specs use:\n53: \n54: ```text\n55: {spec_folder}/research/\n56: ```\n57: \n58: Child-phase and sub-phase targets use flat-first behavior:\n59: \n60: - first run with an empty local `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`;\n61: - a `{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-NN` subfolder is allocated only when prior content already exists for a non-matching target;\n62: - continuation runs reuse the existing matching packet.\n63: \n64: This avoids an unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## 3. OWNERSHIP MODEL\n69: \n70: | Owner | Writes |\n71: |-------|--------|\n72: | Agent iteration | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, JSONL iteration/event append, optional progressive synthesis contribution |\n73: | Workflow reducer | strategy machine-owned sections, findings registry, dashboard |\n74: | Workflow synthesis | `research.md`, lifecycle snapshots |\n75: | Spec anchoring protocol | bounded `spec.md` seed/context/fenced findings block |\n76: \n77: The reducer is the source of truth for derived state. Manual edits to reducer-owned outputs are overwritten on the next refresh.\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 4. FILE PROTECTION\n82: \n83: | Protection | Meaning |\n84: |------------|---------|\n85: | `immutable` | Created once and not modified after init |\n86: | `append-only` | New JSONL records may be appended; existing records are not rewritten |\n87: | `write-once` | Each iteration artifact is created once |\n88: | `mutable` | Workflow may update the file under defined ownership rules |\n89: | `auto-generated` | Reducer/workflow regenerates the full file |\n90: \n91: The config file carries the protection map; details live in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n96: \n97: | Resource | Use When |\n98: |----------|----------|\n99: | `state_jsonl.md` | Need the JSONL config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, or blocked-stop schemas |\n100: | `state_outputs.md` | Need markdown output structure for strategy, iterations, dashboard, research synthesis, or resource map |\n101: | `state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer ownership, registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, or reconstruction |\n102: | `../convergence/convergence.md` | Need STOP contract and legal-stop semantics |\n103: | `../protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` | Need bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back |\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## 6. NON-GOALS\n108: \n109: - Do not document `deep-review` state here; route to the sibling skill.\n110: - Do not treat legacy aliases as write targets. The workflow reads legacy aliases only for migration windows and writes canonical `deep-research-*` names.\n111: - Do not manually edit reducer-owned dashboard or registry files.\n\n(End of file - total 111 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: State Format Reference\ndescription: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\n---\n\n# State Format Reference\n\nLive state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nSummarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","text":"---\ntitle: State Format Reference\ndescription: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\n---\n\n# State Format Reference\n\nLive state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nSummarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\n\n### Routed Details\n\n- `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\n- `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\n- `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\n\nFor iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this skill's live state contract.\n\n### Packet Summary\n\nThe deep-research loop persists continuity in packet files so each iteration can run with fresh context.\n\n| File | Format | Purpose | Mutability |\n|------|--------|---------|------------|\n| `deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters and lineage | Created at init; read-only after |\n| `deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Append-only structured log | Append-only |\n| `deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | Current research plan and next focus | Reducer-managed sections |\n| `deep-research-findings-registry.json` / `findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned findings and question state | Auto-generated |\n| `deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Operator summary | Auto-generated |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration narrative | Write-once |\n| `deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` | JSONL | Per-iteration structured delta | Write-once |\n| `research.md` | Markdown | Final/progressive synthesis | Workflow-owned |\n| `resource-map.md` | Markdown | Optional evidence-derived resource map | Workflow-owned |\n\nThe artifact directory is resolved by `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET LOCATION\n\nRoot specs use:\n\n```text\n{spec_folder}/research/\n```\n\nChild-phase and sub-phase targets use flat-first behavior:\n\n- first run with an empty local `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`;\n- a `{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-NN` subfolder is allocated only when prior content already exists for a non-matching target;\n- continuation runs reuse the existing matching packet.\n\nThis avoids an unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n\n---\n\n## 3. OWNERSHIP MODEL\n\n| Owner | Writes |\n|-------|--------|\n| Agent iteration | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, JSONL iteration/event append, optional progressive synthesis contribution |\n| Workflow reducer | strategy machine-owned sections, findings registry, dashboard |\n| Workflow synthesis | `research.md`, lifecycle snapshots |\n| Spec anchoring protocol | bounded `spec.md` seed/context/fenced findings block |\n\nThe reducer is the source of truth for derived state. Manual edits to reducer-owned outputs are overwritten on the next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FILE PROTECTION\n\n| Protection | Meaning |\n|------------|---------|\n| `immutable` | Created once and not modified after init |\n| `append-only` | New JSONL records may be appended; existing records are not rewritten |\n| `write-once` | Each iteration artifact is created once |\n| `mutable` | Workflow may update the file under defined ownership rules |\n| `auto-generated` | Reducer/workflow regenerates the full file |\n\nThe config file carries the protection map; details live in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n\n| Resource | Use When |\n|----------|----------|\n| `state_jsonl.md` | Need the JSONL config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, or blocked-stop schemas |\n| `state_outputs.md` | Need markdown output structure for strategy, iterations, dashboard, research synthesis, or resource map |\n| `state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer ownership, registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, or reconstruction |\n| `../convergence/convergence.md` | Need STOP contract and legal-stop semantics |\n| `../protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` | Need bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back |\n\n---\n\n## 6. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not document `deep-review` state here; route to the sibling skill.\n- Do not treat legacy aliases as write targets. The workflow reads legacy aliases only for migration windows and writes canonical `deep-research-*` names.\n- Do not manually edit reducer-owned dashboard or registry files.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":111,"totalLines":111,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","time":{"start":1780735949676,"end":1780735949683}},"id":"prt_e9c22392b001sWSkBCUKYbsgRs","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c220e13001CizcxDAsggJ3Ev"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735950406,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_05_BVe19aB8M0OrUuIiiKrN8720","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n3: description: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n7: \n8: `deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n13: \n14: ### Purpose\n15: \n16: Define the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n17: \n18: ### When to Use\n19: \n20: Load this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n21: \n22: ### Core Principle\n23: \n24: Raw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n29: \n30: The config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n31: \n32: ```json\n33: {\n34:   \"type\": \"config\",\n35:   \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n36:   \"maxIterations\": 10,\n37:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n38:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n39:   \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n40:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n41: }\n42: ```\n43: \n44: The full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n49: \n50: ```json\n51: {\n52:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n53:   \"run\": 1,\n54:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n55:   \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n56:   \"findingsCount\": 5,\n57:   \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n58:   \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n59:   \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n60:   \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n61:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n62:   \"durationMs\": 45000\n63: }\n64: ```\n65: \n66: | Field | Required | Notes |\n67: |-------|----------|-------|\n68: | `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n69: | `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n70: | `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n71: | `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n72: | `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n73: | `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n74: | `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n75: | `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n76: | `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n77: | `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n78: | `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n79: \n80: Status values:\n81: \n82: | Status | Meaning |\n83: |--------|---------|\n84: | `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n85: | `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n86: | `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n87: | `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n88: | `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n89: | `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n94: \n95: When the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n96: \n97: ```json\n98: {\n99:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n100:   \"run\": 5,\n101:   \"convergenceSignals\": {\n102:     \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n103:     \"madScore\": 0.08,\n104:     \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n105:     \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n106:   }\n107: }\n108: ```\n109: \n110: Signal rules live in `../convergence/convergence_signals.md`.\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n115: \n116: Use `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n117: \n118: ```json\n119: {\n120:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n121:   \"run\": 3,\n122:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n123:   \"ruledOut\": [\n124:     {\n125:       \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n126:       \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n127:       \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n128:     }\n129:   ]\n130: }\n131: ```\n132: \n133: Ruled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n138: \n139: `graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n140: \n141: ```json\n142: {\n143:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n144:   \"run\": 4,\n145:   \"graphEvents\": [\n146:     {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n147:     {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n148:     {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n149:   ]\n150: }\n151: ```\n152: \n153: Valid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n158: \n159: Lifecycle event:\n160: \n161: ```json\n162: {\n163:   \"type\": \"event\",\n164:   \"event\": \"resumed\",\n165:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n166:   \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n167:   \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n168:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n169:   \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n170:   \"generation\": 1,\n171:   \"archivedPath\": null,\n172:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n173: }\n174: ```\n175: \n176: Blocked stop event:\n177: \n178: ```json\n179: {\n180:   \"type\": \"event\",\n181:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n182:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n183:   \"run\": 7,\n184:   \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n185:   \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n186:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n187:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n188: }\n189: ```\n190: \n191: Pause event:\n192: \n193: ```json\n194: {\n195:   \"type\": \"event\",\n196:   \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n197:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n198:   \"run\": 7,\n199:   \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n200:   \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n201:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n202: }\n203: ```\n204: \n205: Stuck recovery event:\n206: \n207: ```json\n208: {\n209:   \"type\": \"event\",\n210:   \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n211:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n212:   \"run\": 7,\n213:   \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n214:   \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n215:   \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n216:   \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n217:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n218: }\n219: ```\n220: \n221: Graph convergence event shape lives in `../convergence/convergence_graph.md`.\n222: \n223: ---\n224: \n225: ## 8. NORMALIZATION\n226: \n227: Emission-time normalization maps legacy labels into canonical `stopReason` values before persistence. The mapping lives in `../convergence/convergence.md`.\n228: \n229: Malformed lines are handled by the reducer according to its strict/lenient mode. Fault tolerance and reconstruction are documented in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n(End of file - total 229 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nRaw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n\nThe config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"config\",\n  \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 1,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n  \"findingsCount\": 5,\n  \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n  \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n  \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n  \"durationMs\": 45000\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Required | Notes |\n|-------|----------|-------|\n| `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n| `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n| `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n| `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n| `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n| `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n| `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n| `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n| `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n| `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n| `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n\nStatus values:\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n|--------|---------|\n| `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n| `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n| `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n| `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n| `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n| `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n\n---\n\n## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n\nWhen the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 5,\n  \"convergenceSignals\": {\n    \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n    \"madScore\": 0.08,\n    \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n    \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSignal rules live in `../convergence/convergence_signals.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n\nUse `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 3,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"ruledOut\": [\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n      \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n      \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nRuled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n\n---\n\n## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n\n`graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 4,\n  \"graphEvents\": [\n    {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n    {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n    {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nValid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n\n---\n\n## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n\nLifecycle event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"archivedPath\": null,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nBlocked stop event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nPause event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nStuck recovery event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n  \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n  \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nGraph convergence event shape lives in `../convergence/convergence_graph.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. NORMALIZATION\n\nEmission-time normalization maps legacy labels into canonical `stopReason` values before persistence. The mapping lives in `../convergence/convergence.md`.\n\nMalformed lines are handled by the reducer according to its strict/lenient mode. Fault tolerance and reconstruction are documented in `state_reducer_registry.md`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":229,"totalLines":229,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","time":{"start":1780735950387,"end":1780735950403}},"id":"prt_e9c223bec0013LuLvEu1kttU8y","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c220e13001CizcxDAsggJ3Ev"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780735950864,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"id":"prt_e9c22400e001NhJikXb0F7CuOe","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"1023e537ff2fd3a66e3247e1035c2c65cb3f682e","messageID":"msg_e9c220e13001CizcxDAsggJ3Ev","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":45158,"input":8299,"output":422,"reasoning":213,"cache":{"write":0,"read":36224}},"cost":0.004293827}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780735952192,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"id":"prt_e9c22453d001L6Qb7keOx4AIiW","messageID":"msg_e9c22410b001QFp57xF7YC5lp0","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","snapshot":"1023e537ff2fd3a66e3247e1035c2c65cb3f682e","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735964758,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_2hvQrpW50pWDh7PpXwQn7363","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-config.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions: KQ1 parity matrix for all 37 tools with a CLI equivalent per tool (prior art: generate-context.js already does memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs under scripts/dist/memory/); KQ2 daemon-dependency audit (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs — what dies per architecture); KQ3 MCP-only affordances and replacements (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable plus session-proxy replay semantics); KQ4 integration-surface migration (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap and memory_context, agents allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools); KQ5 comparison of a/b/c with effort estimates, risk register, go/no-go recommendation. Evidence: a mid-session MCP disconnect left Claude Code unable to reconnect while a CLI re-bridges per call; the launcher/IPC layer already speaks JSON-RPC over daemon-ipc.sock.\",\n3:   \"maxIterations\": 5,\n4:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0,\n5:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n6:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n7:   \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n8:   \"resource_map_present\": false,\n9:   \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": true },\n10:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\n11:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n12:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n13:   \"lineage\": {\n14:     \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\n15:     \"parentSessionId\": null,\n16:     \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n17:     \"generation\": 1,\n18:     \"continuedFromRun\": null\n19:   },\n20:   \"fanout\": {\n21:     \"executors\": [\n22:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"deepseek\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5 },\n23:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"minimax\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5, \"timeoutSeconds\": 1500 },\n24:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"mimo\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5 }\n25:     ],\n26:     \"concurrency\": 2\n27:   }\n28: }\n\n(End of file - total 28 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions: KQ1 parity matrix for all 37 tools with a CLI equivalent per tool (prior art: generate-context.js already does memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs under scripts/dist/memory/); KQ2 daemon-dependency audit (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs — what dies per architecture); KQ3 MCP-only affordances and replacements (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable plus session-proxy replay semantics); KQ4 integration-surface migration (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap and memory_context, agents allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools); KQ5 comparison of a/b/c with effort estimates, risk register, go/no-go recommendation. Evidence: a mid-session MCP disconnect left Claude Code unable to reconnect while a CLI re-bridges per call; the launcher/IPC layer already speaks JSON-RPC over daemon-ipc.sock.\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 5,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": true },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": null,\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"fanout\": {","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions: KQ1 parity matrix for all 37 tools with a CLI equivalent per tool (prior art: generate-context.js already does memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs under scripts/dist/memory/); KQ2 daemon-dependency audit (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs — what dies per architecture); KQ3 MCP-only affordances and replacements (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable plus session-proxy replay semantics); KQ4 integration-surface migration (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap and memory_context, agents allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools); KQ5 comparison of a/b/c with effort estimates, risk register, go/no-go recommendation. Evidence: a mid-session MCP disconnect left Claude Code unable to reconnect while a CLI re-bridges per call; the launcher/IPC layer already speaks JSON-RPC over daemon-ipc.sock.\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 5,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": true },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": null,\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"fanout\": {\n    \"executors\": [\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"deepseek\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5 },\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"minimax\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5, \"timeoutSeconds\": 1500 },\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"mimo\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5 }\n    ],\n    \"concurrency\": 2\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":28,"totalLines":28,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-config.json","time":{"start":1780735964731,"end":1780735964756}},"id":"prt_e9c22739d001IJq1I736kK9g0o","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c22410b001QFp57xF7YC5lp0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735965424,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_qqDeQyna8Ti18GNh5iOw8010","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-state.jsonl"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-state.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions (parity matrix, daemon-dependency audit, MCP-only affordances, integration-surface migration, architecture comparison with go/no-go).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"}\n2: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fanout_mode\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"lineages\":[\"deepseek\",\"minimax\",\"mimo\"],\"concurrency\":2,\"perLineageIterations\":5,\"sessionId\":\"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\"}\n\n(End of file - total 2 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions (parity matrix, daemon-dependency audit, MCP-only affordances, integration-surface migration, architecture comparison with go/no-go).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fanout_mode\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"lineages\":[\"deepseek\",\"minimax\",\"mimo\"],\"concurrency\":2,\"perLineageIterations\":5,\"sessionId\":\"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\"}","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-state.jsonl","text":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions (parity matrix, daemon-dependency audit, MCP-only affordances, integration-surface migration, architecture comparison with go/no-go).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fanout_mode\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"lineages\":[\"deepseek\",\"minimax\",\"mimo\"],\"concurrency\":2,\"perLineageIterations\":5,\"sessionId\":\"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\"}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":2,"totalLines":2,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-state.jsonl","time":{"start":1780735965417,"end":1780735965423}},"id":"prt_e9c2276a10013TQYzqjt4Mu8B6","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c22410b001QFp57xF7YC5lp0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735966113,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_QGj8iucpqfnbOAK1ZETf8194","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy\n2: \n3: ## Topic\n4: \n5: Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar.\n6: \n7: ## Key Questions\n8: \n9: - [ ] KQ1: What is the CLI equivalent for each of the 37 MCP tools (full parity matrix)? Prior art: `generate-context.js` already performs memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs exist under `scripts/dist/memory/`.\n10: - [ ] KQ2: Which features depend on a long-lived daemon (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs), and what dies under each architecture?\n11: - [ ] KQ3: Which affordances exist ONLY because of the MCP protocol (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable + session-proxy replay), and what are the concrete CLI replacements?\n12: - [ ] KQ4: What does migrating every current MCP caller entail (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap/memory_context, agents' allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools)?\n13: - [ ] KQ5: How do architectures a/b/c compare on the zero-feature-loss bar, effort, and risk — and what is the go/no-go recommendation?\n14: \n15: ## Known Context\n16: \n17: Verified facts available at init (from pre-run exploration of this repo; lanes should re-verify citations independently):\n18: - The MCP server registers 37 tools across 5 registry files under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/` (memory 16, context 1, causal 4, checkpoint 4, lifecycle 12).\n19: - The launcher/daemon layer (`.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` + `lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` + `lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`) already speaks JSON-RPC over a unix socket (`daemon-ipc.sock`); the MCP-protocol-specific surface is the stdio transport + tool schemas + session-proxy replay classification.\n20: - Daemon-resident services: local-first embedding cascade (ollama → hf-local → OpenAI → Voyage) with warm model server, chokidar file-watcher, async embedding retry queue, RSS watchdog with in-place recycle, owner-lease single-writer model.\n21: - CLI prior art: `scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` (canonical save), plus reindex/cleanup/validate/backfill/rank maintenance CLIs.\n22: - Operational evidence FOR de-MCP-ing: 2026-06-06 mid-session MCP disconnect (owner session closed; bridged secondary rode the ~41s reattach ladder, gave up, and Claude Code never reconnects MCP mid-session — 45 tools lost for the session). A per-call CLI would have re-bridged.\n23: - Evidence AGAINST / costs: MCP gives agents automatic tool discovery + schemas + per-tool permission gating; hooks and agents across 4 runtimes currently call MCP tools directly.\n24: \n25: ## Negative Knowledge (ruled out)\n26: \n27: - (none yet)\n28: \n29: ## Next Focus\n30: \n31: Start with KQ1 (parity matrix) and KQ2 (daemon-dependency audit) — they anchor every other question.\n32: \n33: ## Parameters\n34: \n35: - Max iterations: 5 (per lane, terminal cap)\n36: - Convergence threshold: 0 (forced full iteration budget; legal early stop only via all-questions-answered)\n\n(End of file - total 36 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy\n\n## Topic\n\nCan the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [ ] KQ1: What is the CLI equivalent for each of the 37 MCP tools (full parity matrix)? Prior art: `generate-context.js` already performs memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs exist under `scripts/dist/memory/`.\n- [ ] KQ2: Which features depend on a long-lived daemon (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs), and what dies under each architecture?\n- [ ] KQ3: Which affordances exist ONLY because of the MCP protocol (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable + session-proxy replay), and what are the concrete CLI replacements?\n- [ ] KQ4: What does migrating every current MCP caller entail (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap/memory_context, agents' allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools)?\n- [ ] KQ5: How do architectures a/b/c compare on the zero-feature-loss bar, effort, and risk — and what is the go/no-go recommendation?\n\n## Known Context\n\nVerified facts available at init (from pre-run exploration of this repo; lanes should re-verify citations independently):\n- The MCP server registers 37 tools across 5 registry files under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/` (memory 16, context 1, causal 4, checkpoint 4, lifecycle 12).\n- The launcher/daemon layer (`.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` + `lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` + `lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`) already speaks JSON-RPC over a unix socket (`daemon-ipc.sock`); the MCP-protocol-specific surface is the stdio transport + tool schemas + session-proxy replay classification.\n- Daemon-resident services: local-first embedding cascade (ollama → hf-local → OpenAI → Voyage) with warm model server, chokidar file-watcher, async embedding retry queue, RSS watchdog with in-place recycle, owner-lease single-writer model.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy\n\n## Topic\n\nCan the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [ ] KQ1: What is the CLI equivalent for each of the 37 MCP tools (full parity matrix)? Prior art: `generate-context.js` already performs memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs exist under `scripts/dist/memory/`.\n- [ ] KQ2: Which features depend on a long-lived daemon (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs), and what dies under each architecture?\n- [ ] KQ3: Which affordances exist ONLY because of the MCP protocol (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable + session-proxy replay), and what are the concrete CLI replacements?\n- [ ] KQ4: What does migrating every current MCP caller entail (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap/memory_context, agents' allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools)?\n- [ ] KQ5: How do architectures a/b/c compare on the zero-feature-loss bar, effort, and risk — and what is the go/no-go recommendation?\n\n## Known Context\n\nVerified facts available at init (from pre-run exploration of this repo; lanes should re-verify citations independently):\n- The MCP server registers 37 tools across 5 registry files under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/` (memory 16, context 1, causal 4, checkpoint 4, lifecycle 12).\n- The launcher/daemon layer (`.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` + `lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` + `lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`) already speaks JSON-RPC over a unix socket (`daemon-ipc.sock`); the MCP-protocol-specific surface is the stdio transport + tool schemas + session-proxy replay classification.\n- Daemon-resident services: local-first embedding cascade (ollama → hf-local → OpenAI → Voyage) with warm model server, chokidar file-watcher, async embedding retry queue, RSS watchdog with in-place recycle, owner-lease single-writer model.\n- CLI prior art: `scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` (canonical save), plus reindex/cleanup/validate/backfill/rank maintenance CLIs.\n- Operational evidence FOR de-MCP-ing: 2026-06-06 mid-session MCP disconnect (owner session closed; bridged secondary rode the ~41s reattach ladder, gave up, and Claude Code never reconnects MCP mid-session — 45 tools lost for the session). A per-call CLI would have re-bridged.\n- Evidence AGAINST / costs: MCP gives agents automatic tool discovery + schemas + per-tool permission gating; hooks and agents across 4 runtimes currently call MCP tools directly.\n\n## Negative Knowledge (ruled out)\n\n- (none yet)\n\n## Next Focus\n\nStart with KQ1 (parity matrix) and KQ2 (daemon-dependency audit) — they anchor every other question.\n\n## Parameters\n\n- Max iterations: 5 (per lane, terminal cap)\n- Convergence threshold: 0 (forced full iteration budget; legal early stop only via all-questions-answered)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":36,"totalLines":36,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1780735966103,"end":1780735966110}},"id":"prt_e9c227952001H3Pb0E3s34tpqx","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c22410b001QFp57xF7YC5lp0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735966755,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_03_GKDXSJGe7NybIPgJzY4a8700","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\ndeepseek/\nminimax/\n\n(2 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"deepseek/\nminimax/","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages","entries":["deepseek/","minimax/"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":2,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages","time":{"start":1780735966744,"end":1780735966754}},"id":"prt_e9c227c0e001enovgO1hyWwYOy","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c22410b001QFp57xF7YC5lp0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735967435,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_04_NN5gaoQLWJLRXcGgQv0p4341","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Implementation Plan: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility [system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan]\"\n3: description: \"Single-execution research plan: one /deep:start-research-loop:auto fan-out invocation with three CLI lanes (DeepSeek-v4-pro, MiniMax-M3, MiMo-V2.5-Pro), 5 forced iterations each, concurrency 2.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"mcp cli feasibility plan\"\n6:   - \"fan-out research plan\"\n7:   - \"three lane research\"\n8: importance_tier: \"normal\"\n9: contextType: \"general\"\n10: _memory:\n11:   continuity:\n12:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"\n13:     last_updated_at: \"2026-06-06T12:30:00Z\"\n14:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n15:     recent_action: \"Authored the research run plan\"\n16:     next_safe_action: \"Launch the 3-lane deep-research fan-out loop\"\n17:     blockers: []\n18:     key_files:\n19:       - \"plan.md\"\n20:     completion_pct: 0\n21:     open_questions: []\n22:     answered_questions: []\n23: ---\n24: # Implementation Plan: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility\n25: \n26: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 1 -->\n27: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: plan-core | v2.2 -->\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: <!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n32: ## 1. SUMMARY\n33: \n34: ### Technical Context\n35: \n36: | Aspect | Value |\n37: |--------|-------|\n38: | **Language/Stack** | deep-loop-runtime (Node CJS) orchestrating cli-opencode lanes |\n39: | **Framework** | `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` fan-out (one lineage per model) |\n40: | **Storage** | File-based JSONL state + registries under `research/` |\n41: | **Testing** | `validate.sh --strict` + `orchestration-summary.json` lane outcomes |\n42: \n43: ### Overview\n44: One fan-out invocation runs three heterogeneous research lanes against the same topic, each with a forced 5-iteration terminal cap, then merges findings and compiles the verdict report. There are no implementation phases: this packet ships research, not code.\n45: <!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: <!-- ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n50: ## 2. QUALITY GATES\n51: \n52: ### Definition of Ready\n53: - [x] Problem statement clear and scope documented\n54: - [x] Success criteria measurable (verdict-shaped report, parity coverage, lane state)\n55: - [x] Dependencies identified (opencode CLI, three provider pools)\n56: \n57: ### Definition of Done\n58: - [ ] All acceptance criteria met (REQ-001..REQ-003 in spec.md)\n59: - [ ] Lane outcomes verified via orchestration summary + per-lane state\n60: - [ ] Docs updated (spec/tasks/implementation-summary) and final strict validation passes\n61: <!-- /ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: <!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n66: ## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n67: \n68: ### Pattern\n69: Command-owned research loop with fan-out lineages (no application architecture changes).\n70: \n71: ### Key Components\n72: - **Orchestrator**: `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` resolves setup, spawns lanes, merges, compiles.\n73: - **Lane pool**: `fanout-run.cjs` capped pool (concurrency 2), one opencode subprocess per lane; DeepSeek lane gets `--pure` natively; reasoning effort maps to `--variant high`.\n74: - **Lanes**: deepseek (`deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro`), minimax (`minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`, 1500s per-iteration ceiling), mimo (`xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`).\n75: - **Merge + compile**: `fanout-merge.cjs` dedups findings by id with lineage attribution; reducer compiles `research.md`.\n76: \n77: ### Data Flow\n78: Topic -> per-lane lineage configs (`research/lineages/{label}/`) -> 5 read-only investigation iterations per lane -> per-lane findings registries -> merged registry + attribution -> compiled `research/research.md` + generated spec-findings fence in spec.md.\n79: <!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: <!-- ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->\n84: ## FIX ADDENDUM: AFFECTED SURFACES\n85: \n86: Not applicable: this packet is research-only (`research_intent=feasibility`), no bug fix, no code mutation. Lanes are read-only investigators; the only writes are workflow-owned artifacts under `research/` plus the bounded generated block in spec.md.\n87: \n88: | Surface | Current Role | Action | Verification |\n89: |---------|--------------|--------|--------------|\n90: | research/** | workflow artifact tree | create (workflow-owned) | orchestration-summary.json + validate.sh |\n91: | mk-spec-memory runtime | research subject | unchanged (read-only evidence source) | git status clean outside the packet |\n92: <!-- /ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: <!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n97: ## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n98: \n99: ### Phase 1: Setup\n100: - [x] Packet folder + four core docs authored from v2.2 templates\n101: - [x] description.json + graph-metadata.json generated\n102: - [x] Pre-run `validate.sh --strict` passes (2026-06-06, 0 errors 0 warnings)\n103: \n104: ### Phase 2: Core Execution\n105: - [ ] Launch the fan-out invocation (exact command in tasks.md T003 / approved plan file)\n106: - [ ] Monitor `research/orchestration-status.log` + per-lane iteration files to completion\n107: \n108: ### Phase 3: Verification\n109: - [ ] Merged registry + fanout-attribution.md present; research.md verdict-shaped\n110: - [ ] Per-lane iteration counts recorded; early-stopped lanes documented\n111: - [ ] Reconciliation: tasks ticked, metadata regenerated, final strict validation, continuity saved via generate-context.js\n112: <!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: <!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n117: ## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n118: \n119: | Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n120: |-----------|-------|-------|\n121: | Structural | Packet docs + anchors | validate.sh --strict |\n122: | Lane health | 3 lanes, exit codes 0/2/3, salvage sweeps | orchestration-status.log, orchestration-summary.json |\n123: | Content | Verdict shape: parity matrix, loss table, go/no-go | Manual review against REQ-002/REQ-003 |\n124: <!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: <!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n129: ## 6. DEPENDENCIES\n130: \n131: | Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |\n132: |------------|------|--------|-------------------|\n133: | opencode CLI 1.16.2 | External | Green | No lanes can run |\n134: | deepseek-api / minimax-token-plan / xiaomi-token-plan pools | External | Green (smoke-tested 2026-06-06) | Affected lane fails; partial merge path applies |\n135: | deep-loop-runtime fan-out scripts | Internal | Green | Fall back to three sequential single-executor loops |\n136: <!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: <!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->\n141: ## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN\n142: \n143: - **Trigger**: Run produces unusable output or must be abandoned mid-flight.\n144: - **Procedure**: Research-only rollback: stop lanes (pool SIGTERM honors salvage), delete or archive `research/` outputs, revert packet docs via git. No production system is touched.\n145: <!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->\n\n(End of file - total 145 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Implementation Plan: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility [system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan]\"\ndescription: \"Single-execution research plan: one /deep:start-research-loop:auto fan-out invocation with three CLI lanes (DeepSeek-v4-pro, MiniMax-M3, MiMo-V2.5-Pro), 5 forced iterations each, concurrency 2.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"mcp cli feasibility plan\"\n  - \"fan-out research plan\"\n  - \"three lane research\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"general\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-06T12:30:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n    recent_action: \"Authored the research run plan\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Launch the 3-lane deep-research fan-out loop\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files:\n      - \"plan.md\"\n    completion_pct: 0","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Implementation Plan: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility [system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan]\"\ndescription: \"Single-execution research plan: one /deep:start-research-loop:auto fan-out invocation with three CLI lanes (DeepSeek-v4-pro, MiniMax-M3, MiMo-V2.5-Pro), 5 forced iterations each, concurrency 2.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"mcp cli feasibility plan\"\n  - \"fan-out research plan\"\n  - \"three lane research\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"general\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-06T12:30:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n    recent_action: \"Authored the research run plan\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Launch the 3-lane deep-research fan-out loop\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files:\n      - \"plan.md\"\n    completion_pct: 0\n    open_questions: []\n    answered_questions: []\n---\n# Implementation Plan: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 1 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: plan-core | v2.2 -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n## 1. SUMMARY\n\n### Technical Context\n\n| Aspect | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| **Language/Stack** | deep-loop-runtime (Node CJS) orchestrating cli-opencode lanes |\n| **Framework** | `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` fan-out (one lineage per model) |\n| **Storage** | File-based JSONL state + registries under `research/` |\n| **Testing** | `validate.sh --strict` + `orchestration-summary.json` lane outcomes |\n\n### Overview\nOne fan-out invocation runs three heterogeneous research lanes against the same topic, each with a forced 5-iteration terminal cap, then merges findings and compiles the verdict report. There are no implementation phases: this packet ships research, not code.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n## 2. QUALITY GATES\n\n### Definition of Ready\n- [x] Problem statement clear and scope documented\n- [x] Success criteria measurable (verdict-shaped report, parity coverage, lane state)\n- [x] Dependencies identified (opencode CLI, three provider pools)\n\n### Definition of Done\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria met (REQ-001..REQ-003 in spec.md)\n- [ ] Lane outcomes verified via orchestration summary + per-lane state\n- [ ] Docs updated (spec/tasks/implementation-summary) and final strict validation passes\n<!-- /ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n### Pattern\nCommand-owned research loop with fan-out lineages (no application architecture changes).\n\n### Key Components\n- **Orchestrator**: `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` resolves setup, spawns lanes, merges, compiles.\n- **Lane pool**: `fanout-run.cjs` capped pool (concurrency 2), one opencode subprocess per lane; DeepSeek lane gets `--pure` natively; reasoning effort maps to `--variant high`.\n- **Lanes**: deepseek (`deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro`), minimax (`minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`, 1500s per-iteration ceiling), mimo (`xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`).\n- **Merge + compile**: `fanout-merge.cjs` dedups findings by id with lineage attribution; reducer compiles `research.md`.\n\n### Data Flow\nTopic -> per-lane lineage configs (`research/lineages/{label}/`) -> 5 read-only investigation iterations per lane -> per-lane findings registries -> merged registry + attribution -> compiled `research/research.md` + generated spec-findings fence in spec.md.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->\n## FIX ADDENDUM: AFFECTED SURFACES\n\nNot applicable: this packet is research-only (`research_intent=feasibility`), no bug fix, no code mutation. Lanes are read-only investigators; the only writes are workflow-owned artifacts under `research/` plus the bounded generated block in spec.md.\n\n| Surface | Current Role | Action | Verification |\n|---------|--------------|--------|--------------|\n| research/** | workflow artifact tree | create (workflow-owned) | orchestration-summary.json + validate.sh |\n| mk-spec-memory runtime | research subject | unchanged (read-only evidence source) | git status clean outside the packet |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n\n### Phase 1: Setup\n- [x] Packet folder + four core docs authored from v2.2 templates\n- [x] description.json + graph-metadata.json generated\n- [x] Pre-run `validate.sh --strict` passes (2026-06-06, 0 errors 0 warnings)\n\n### Phase 2: Core Execution\n- [ ] Launch the fan-out invocation (exact command in tasks.md T003 / approved plan file)\n- [ ] Monitor `research/orchestration-status.log` + per-lane iteration files to completion\n\n### Phase 3: Verification\n- [ ] Merged registry + fanout-attribution.md present; research.md verdict-shaped\n- [ ] Per-lane iteration counts recorded; early-stopped lanes documented\n- [ ] Reconciliation: tasks ticked, metadata regenerated, final strict validation, continuity saved via generate-context.js\n<!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n\n| Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n|-----------|-------|-------|\n| Structural | Packet docs + anchors | validate.sh --strict |\n| Lane health | 3 lanes, exit codes 0/2/3, salvage sweeps | orchestration-status.log, orchestration-summary.json |\n| Content | Verdict shape: parity matrix, loss table, go/no-go | Manual review against REQ-002/REQ-003 |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n## 6. DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |\n|------------|------|--------|-------------------|\n| opencode CLI 1.16.2 | External | Green | No lanes can run |\n| deepseek-api / minimax-token-plan / xiaomi-token-plan pools | External | Green (smoke-tested 2026-06-06) | Affected lane fails; partial merge path applies |\n| deep-loop-runtime fan-out scripts | Internal | Green | Fall back to three sequential single-executor loops |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->\n## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN\n\n- **Trigger**: Run produces unusable output or must be abandoned mid-flight.\n- **Procedure**: Research-only rollback: stop lanes (pool SIGTERM honors salvage), delete or archive `research/` outputs, revert packet docs via git. No production system is touched.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":145,"totalLines":145,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan.md","time":{"start":1780735967415,"end":1780735967433}},"id":"prt_e9c227eb1001XAJZfl4RMuX7yq","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c22410b001QFp57xF7YC5lp0"}}
