{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780736029408,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_dk5ldxIZkNFFw6dmGTqB5909","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/deep-research-config.json","content":"{\n  \"topic\": \"Feasibility: Can the mk-spec-memory MCP (37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with zero feature loss? Evaluate architectures (a) pure CLI, (b) CLI-over-daemon, (c) hybrid CLI.\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 5,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": true },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"fanout-deepseek-1780735927714-4462h3\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n    \"label\": \"deepseek\"\n  },\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\",\n    \"model\": \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\"\n  }\n}\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/deep-research-config.json","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/deep-research-config.json","time":{"start":1780736029399,"end":1780736029406}},"id":"prt_e9c2360f0001Rdaionsf4aREHD","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c235725001p1aBrYxZJsYqp5"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780736033452,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_01_XTE3tiRrnfRRnC9Mf90b3534","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/deep-research-state.jsonl","content":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Feasibility: Can the mk-spec-memory MCP (37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with zero feature loss?\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-deepseek-1780735927714-4462h3\",\"label\":\"deepseek\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lineage_init\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-deepseek-1780735927714-4462h3\",\"parentSessionId\":\"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"label\":\"deepseek\",\"executor\":\"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\"}\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/deep-research-state.jsonl","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/deep-research-state.jsonl","time":{"start":1780736033448,"end":1780736033451}},"id":"prt_e9c237310001zOZmRpO4k11FdI","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c235725001p1aBrYxZJsYqp5"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780736048126,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_02_7smkjbV3FnQwerkbVMbq3332","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/deep-research-strategy.md","content":"# Deep Research Strategy (DeepSeek Lane)\n\n## Topic\n\nCan the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [ ] KQ1: Parity matrix for all 37 MCP tools — CLI equivalent per tool\n- [ ] KQ2: Daemon-dependency audit — what dies under each architecture\n- [ ] KQ3: MCP-only affordances and CLI replacements (discovery, permissioning, Zod validation, retryable errors, session-proxy replay)\n- [ ] KQ4: Integration-surface migration (runtime hooks, agents, /doctor, deep-loop)\n- [ ] KQ5: Architecture comparison with effort estimates, risk register, go/no-go\n\n## Known Context\n\nVerified from codebase exploration:\n- 37 tools in 5 registry modules (memory 16, context 1, causal 4, checkpoint 4, lifecycle 12)\n- Launcher at `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs`: owner-lease single-writer, IPC bridge over `daemon-ipc.sock`, RSS watchdog with in-place recycle, crash-loop detection, respawn after dead socket\n- Session proxy at `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`: reconnecting MCP proxy with replay classification (REPLAYABLE_TOOL_NAMES, UNSAFE_TOOL_NAMES), keepalive pings, protocol version check, JSON-RPC frame splitter\n- IPC bridge at `.opencode/bin/lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs`: `getIpcSocketPath()`, `probeDaemon()` with deep JSON-RPC probe, `probeModelServer()` with HTTP health check, `bridgeStdioToSocket()`\n- Daemon context-server at `mcp_server/dist/context-server.js`: full MCP stdio server, tool dispatch, chokidar file-watcher, async embedding retry queue, session priming, auto-surface memories, token budget enforcement\n- CLI prior art: `generate-context.js` performs memory_save; no other operational CLIs found in `scripts/dist/` (only test scripts exist)\n- The launcher/IPC layer already speaks JSON-RPC over a unix socket — the MCP-specific surface is the stdio transport + Zod-validated tool schemas + session-proxy replay classification\n\n## Negative Knowledge (ruled out)\n\n- (none yet)\n\n## Non-Goals\n\nThis is a research-only lane: no CLI implementation, no code changes, no benchmarks. Only file:line evidence and architectural analysis.\n\n## Stop Conditions\n\n- 5 iterations completed (terminal cap)\n- All 5 key questions answered with evidence\n- Convergence threshold 0 (forced full budget)\n\n## Next Focus\n\nStart with KQ1 (parity matrix) — read all 37 tool definitions, handlers, and schemas to classify each tool as: purely stateless (trivially CLI-portable), stateful-but-sync (CLI-portable), or daemon-dependent (requires architecture b or c).\n\n## Parameters\n\n- Max iterations: 5\n- Convergence threshold: 0\n- Executor: DeepSeek-v4-pro via cli-opencode\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/deep-research-strategy.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1780736048107,"end":1780736048124}},"id":"prt_e9c238322001e2fJLGg7xQ0ERw","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c235725001p1aBrYxZJsYqp5"}}
