directly - NEVER through Code Mode. Use it only after the canonical packet is still thin; use anchored memory_search() only for targeted gap filling.\"\n\n  Line 149:     outputs: { memory_loaded: true, context_source: \"handover|continuity|spec_docs|memory_context|memory_search\", context_summary: extracted_context, resume_packet: \"now|last|next|blockers|artifact\" }\n\n  Line 194:   memory_search_failed: { action: \"Proceed only with essentials already recovered\", fallback: \"Offer /speckit:resume <spec-folder> or start fresh\" }\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_confirm.yaml:\n  Line 309:     tool: memory_search\n\n  Line 330:       note: \"Use Code Graph structural queries (code_graph_query) + Grep to verify plan references against codebase patterns; verify hits with Read. memory_search is for spec docs/memory, not arbitrary code.\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_confirm.yaml:\n  Line 370:       - { id: memory_context, points: 20 }\n\n  Line 476:     tool: memory_search\n\n  Line 729:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\n\n  Line 738:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\n\n  Line 747:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\n\n  Line 756:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_auto.yaml:\n  Line 332:     tool: memory_search\n\n  Line 348:       note: \"Use Code Graph structural queries (code_graph_query) + Grep to verify plan references against codebase patterns; verify hits with Read. memory_search is for spec docs/memory, not arbitrary code.\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_auto.yaml:\n  Line 352:       - { id: memory_context, points: 20 }\n\n  Line 449:     tool: memory_search\n\n  Line 685:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\n\n  Line 694:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\n\n  Line 703:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\n\n  Line 712:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ask-ai-council_confirm.yaml:\n  Line 34:     tool: memory_context\n\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 101 matches (1 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":101,"truncated":true},"title":"mk-spec-memory|memory_search|memory_context|session_bootstrap","time":{"start":1780736069449,"end":1780736069530}},"id":"prt_e9c240bd2001B7B2yDb9k9SYnq","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js","messageID":"msg_e9c23f575001FfzCeEuAPaasjU"}}
